(怪诞材料)

52
00:05:20,129 --> 00:05:21,589
(现代精子)

53
00:05:21,839 --> 00:05:24,050
<i>Captain Oveur, white courtesy phone.</i>
欧机长，请接听白色电话

54
00:05:24,342 --> 00:05:27,512
<i>Captain Clarence Oveur,
white courtesy phone.</i>
欧家伦机长，请听白色电话

55
00:05:32,517 --> 00:05:34,602
<i>No, the white phone!</i>
不，白色电话才对

56
00:05:37,814 --> 00:05:38,898
This is Captain Oveur.
我是欧机长

57
00:05:39,148 --> 00:05:41,442
<i>One moment for your call
from the Mayo Clinic.</i>
美奥诊所找你

58
00:05:41,693 --> 00:05:45,029
<i>Captain Oveur, white courtesy phone.</i>
欧机长，请听白色电话

59
00:05:45,280 --> 00:05:47,574
<i>- I've got it!
- Thank you.</i>
-我已在接听
-谢谢

60
00:05:47,824 --> 00:05:49,242
<i>Go ahead with your call.</i>
请接来

61
00:05:49,492 --> 00:05:51,369
<i>This is Dr Brody at the Mayo Clinic.</i>
我是美奥诊所的布医生

62
00:05:51,578 --> 00:05:53,997
There's a passenger
on your Chicago flight,
在你往芝加哥的航机上
有一名乘客

63
00:05:54,289 --> 00:05:57,166
a little girl named Lisa Davis,
en route to Minneapolis.
一个叫戴莉莎的小女孩
是前往明尼阿波利斯的

64
00:05:57,375 --> 00:05:59,294
She's scheduled
for a heart transplant.
她正排期接受心脏移植手术

65
00:05:59,586 --> 00:06:01,629
Tell her mother we found a donor.
告诉她母亲我们找到捐赠者

66
00:06:01,921 --> 00:06:03,673
<i>The heart is ready for surgery.</i>
心脏已准备好移植

67
00:06:03,923 --> 00:06:07,093
<i>We must have the recipient on
the operating table within six hours.</i>
手术得在六小时内进行

68
00:06:07,427 --> 00:06:10,305
Make sure she's kept
in a reclined position,
确保她要躺着

69
00:06:10,555 --> 00:06:13,474
and that a continuous watch
is kept on her IV.
并一直接受静脉注射

70
00:06:13,683 --> 00:06:15,602
<i>It's very important she remain calm...</i>
她保持冷静是很重要的

71
00:06:15,810 --> 00:06:17,770
<i>Excuse me, this is the operator.</i>
对不起，我是接线生

72
00:06:18,062 --> 00:06:21,733
<i>I have an emergency call on line five
from a Mr Hamm.</i>
韩先生急电，在第五线

73
00:06:21,983 --> 00:06:23,943
Give me Hamm on five, hold the Mayo.
替我接进来

74
00:06:50,261 --> 00:06:53,431
You'll be back tomorrow night.
We'll have dinner. We'll talk things over.
你明晚会回来
到时我们共进晚餐好好谈谈

75
00:06:53,723 --> 00:06:56,351
I won't be back.
I've requested the Atlanta run.
我不会回来
我要求调往阿特兰大

76
00:06:56,643 --> 00:06:59,896
Elaine... I promise I can change.
绮莲，我保证我可以改变

77
00:07:00,188 --> 00:07:04,192
Then why didn't you take the job
that Louie Netz offered you at Boeing?
那么为何你不接受李路易
在波音公司给你的工作？

78
00:07:04,484 --> 00:07:07,862
I haven't been able to get
near a plane since the war.
战后我无法走近飞机

79
00:07:08,112 --> 00:07:11,199
And they wouldn't hire me
because of my war record.
加上我的战时记录
他们不会聘用我的

80
00:07:11,449 --> 00:07:14,577
War record? You're the only one
keeping that alive.
战时记录？只有你才在意

81
00:07:14,869 --> 00:07:17,038
For everyone else,
it's ancient history.
其他人都不当这是一回事

82
00:07:17,330 --> 00:07:20,375
- You expect me to believe that?
- It's the truth.
-你以为我会相信？
-那是事实

83
00:07:20,625 --> 00:07:23,253
What's hurt you the most
is your record since the war -
最丢人的是你战后的记录

84
00:07:23,503 --> 00:07:24,963
different cities, different jobs -
往不同城市，做不同工作

85
00:07:25,213 --> 00:07:28,341
and not one of them shows you
can accept any real responsibility.
完全显示了你不可以承担责任

86
00:07:28,633 --> 00:07:31,344
- Elaine, just give me one more...
- It's too late, Ted.
-绮莲，再给我一次…
-太迟了

87
00:07:31,594 --> 00:07:33,513
When I get back to Chicago,
当我返回芝加哥

88
00:07:33,805 --> 00:07:37,308
I'm going to start my life
all over again. I'm sorry.
我要重新生活，抱歉

89
00:07:40,770 --> 00:07:44,148
Excuse me, take this flower
from the Church of Religious...
请收下醒悟教的花朵

90
00:07:53,700 --> 00:07:55,577
Hi! Well, good evening.
你好

91
00:07:55,827 --> 00:07:59,205
There you go.
Just follow them to the back.
行了，跟着他们

92
00:08:02,959 --> 00:08:05,670
Any word on that storm lifting
over Salt Lake, Clarence?
有没有盐湖城那风暴消息？

93
00:08:06,004 --> 00:08:07,672
No, not likely, Victor.
没有

94
00:08:07,922 --> 00:08:12,343
I just reviewed the area report
for 1600 hours through 2400.
我刚看过四点至十二点的
地区报告

95
00:08:12,594 --> 00:08:14,470
There's an occluded front
stalled over the Dakotas,
有一道冷锋在达科他上

96
00:08:14,721 --> 00:08:16,723
backed up all the way to Utah.
一直伸展至犹他

97
00:08:17,056 --> 00:08:20,852
If she decides to push over the Great
Lakes, it could get plenty soupy.
若移至大湖区，就会很大雾

98
00:08:21,060 --> 00:08:22,770
What about that southern route
around Tulsa?
走南路绕过图沙又如何？

99
00:08:23,021 --> 00:08:25,189
I double-checked
the terminal forecast,
我已查看过了

100
00:08:25,481 --> 00:08:28,234
and the wind's aloft
and IFR ceilings all the way.
天气同样恶劣

101
00:08:28,484 --> 00:08:29,944
Where do they top out?
如何恶劣？

102
00:08:30,194 --> 00:08:33,823
Light scattered cover at 20,000,
icing around 18.
二万英尺高空满布密云
一万八千英尺高空更有冰雹

103
00:08:35,241 --> 00:08:39,287
- Looks like over Denver is best.
- Denver it is.
-似乎丹佛的天气最好
-是的

104
00:08:39,579 --> 00:08:40,663
Sorry, Clarence.
抱歉

105
00:08:40,955 --> 00:08:43,875
Latest report shows everything's
socked in from Salt Lake to Lincoln.
最新报告显示由盐湖城至林肯
都很大雾

106
00:08:44,125 --> 00:08:45,668
Hi, Roger. Glad to have you aboard.
罗渣，欢迎你

107
00:08:45,960 --> 00:08:47,670
Victor, this is Roger Murdock.
Victor Basta.
伟达，这是梅罗渣，白伟达

108
00:08:47,921 --> 00:08:49,797
- How do you do?
- Nice to meet you.
-你好吗？
-幸会

109
00:08:50,048 --> 00:08:52,508
I was telling Victor
I reviewed the area report
我正跟伟达说
我看过四点至十二点的…

110
00:08:52,759 --> 00:08:55,303
for 1600 hours through 2400.
地区报告

111
00:08:56,721 --> 00:08:59,474
There's an occluded front
stalled over the Dakotas.
有一道冷锋在达科他上

112
00:08:59,766 --> 00:09:02,018
(美国新闻选举影响)

113
00:09:08,691 --> 00:09:10,735
There you go. Thank you.
行了，谢谢

114
00:09:11,611 --> 00:09:14,072
Is Elaine Dickinson on this flight?
请问狄绮莲在这班机上吗？

115
00:09:14,364 --> 00:09:17,825
The whole flight crew has boarded.
Let me see.
所有机员都登机了，让我看看

116
00:09:19,035 --> 00:09:20,620
Oh, yes. She is on board.
对，她在机上

117
00:09:23,748 --> 00:09:27,252
I'd like one ticket to Chicago.
No baggage.
我想要一张往芝加哥的机票
没有行李

118
00:09:32,882 --> 00:09:36,177
- Smoking or non-smoking?
- Smoking, please.
-吸烟抑或不吸烟？
-吸烟

119
00:09:38,263 --> 00:09:40,556
There. Have a nice trip.
这里，祝旅程愉快

120
00:09:56,072 --> 00:09:58,283
<i>Striker, this is Red Leader Four.</i>
史泰德，这是红队长四号

121
00:09:58,575 --> 00:10:00,660
<i>Primary target covered by fog.</i>
主要目标被大雾遮盖

122
00:10:00,910 --> 00:10:03,037
<i>Decision to proceed is yours.</i>
你要决定继续进行

123
00:10:03,288 --> 00:10:05,707
<i>The decision is yours...</i>
是你决定…

124
00:10:05,915 --> 00:10:08,710
<i>is yours... is yours...</i>
是你…

125
00:10:19,262 --> 00:10:21,889
那白人该远离我妻子

126
00:10:22,223 --> 00:10:23,933
否则我会揍他

127
00:10:24,267 --> 00:10:27,020
对，他不该这样做

128
00:10:27,770 --> 00:10:29,981
我认识一个处境相同的人

129
00:10:30,273 --> 00:10:31,816
结果他后悔莫及

130
00:10:32,358 --> 00:10:34,152
别那么天真了，雅瑟

131
00:10:34,485 --> 00:10:37,947
我们每人都有道德选择

132
00:10:38,948 --> 00:10:40,700
早睡早起

133
00:10:41,034 --> 00:10:43,453
令人健康、富足和聪明

134
00:10:43,745 --> 00:10:46,164
说得真好！

135
00:11:09,103 --> 00:11:10,605
(请勿吸烟)

136
00:11:10,897 --> 00:11:14,609
(扣紧安全带)

137
00:11:22,909 --> 00:11:24,702
Nervous?
很紧张？

138
00:11:24,994 --> 00:11:26,454
Yes.
是的

139
00:11:26,704 --> 00:11:29,040
First time?
第一次？

140
00:11:29,249 --> 00:11:31,709
No. I've been nervous lots of times.
不，已很多次

141
00:11:38,007 --> 00:11:41,594
Hi. We'll be taking off real soon,
so I better fasten you in tight.
我们快起飞了
我替你扣好安全带吧

142
00:11:41,844 --> 00:11:44,472
Thank you.
Oh, Mother, this is so exciting!
劳驾，妈妈，我很兴奋

143
00:11:44,722 --> 00:11:47,392
I know, but remember,
you must get some rest.
我知道，但你得休息

144
00:11:47,600 --> 00:11:51,187
That's good advice. You relax,
and I'll be back after we take off.
你放松点吧！
飞机起飞后我会再回来

145
00:11:51,479 --> 00:11:52,564
Thank you.
谢谢你

146
00:11:55,024 --> 00:11:58,861
- I'm going to miss you so much.
- I'm going to miss you, too.
-我会很想念你
-我也是

147
00:11:59,153 --> 00:12:01,197
Promise you'll write?
答应我写信给我

148
00:12:01,489 --> 00:12:03,241
Every day.
每天都会

149
00:12:04,617 --> 00:12:05,910
Bill!
阿标！

150
00:12:06,160 --> 00:12:08,580
Better get on board, son.
快登机吧

151
00:12:10,081 --> 00:12:11,833
All aboard!
所有乘客登机

152
00:12:12,083 --> 00:12:15,003
209er to ground control.
We're ready to taxi.
209号班机叫地面指挥
我们准备起程

153
00:12:15,295 --> 00:12:17,839
- Goodbye, Bill!
- Goodbye, darling!
-再见，阿标
-再见，宝贝

154
00:12:18,089 --> 00:12:19,757
I love you, darling!
我爱你

155
00:12:19,966 --> 00:12:22,302
<i>209er, taxi to runway19er.</i>
209号班机
请使用第19号跑道

156
00:12:24,887 --> 00:12:26,347
Goodbye, darling!
再见，宝贝

157
00:12:26,639 --> 00:12:29,892
Have your picture taken the minute
you get there and send me one.
你一到步
就要拍照并立即寄给我

158
00:12:30,184 --> 00:12:31,978
OK. Here, hurry.
好的，拿着

159
00:12:34,522 --> 00:12:37,233
It's your watch. You shouldn't.
You're going to need this.
这是你的手表，你不该给我
你会用得着的

160
00:12:37,525 --> 00:12:39,611
It's all right. It doesn't work.
不要紧，已坏掉

161
00:12:39,944 --> 00:12:41,487
- Bill!
- Goodbye, darling!
-阿标
-再见，宝贝

162
00:12:41,779 --> 00:12:43,197
Bill!
阿标！

163
00:12:44,574 --> 00:12:47,577
Bill! Bill!
I'll keep it with me all the time.
阿标，我会整天戴着它

164
00:12:51,164 --> 00:12:53,374
<i>- Flight 209er- clear for takeoff.
- Roger.</i>
-209号班机，可以起飞
-收到

165
00:12:54,417 --> 00:12:57,295
<i>- LA departure frequency 123.9er.
- Roger.</i>
-洛杉矶离开频道是123.9
-收到

166
00:12:58,421 --> 00:13:00,673
- Request vector. Over.
- What?
-请给航向指示
-什么？

167
00:13:00,965 --> 00:13:03,468
<i>Flight 209er, clear for vector 324.</i>
209号班机，可以起飞了

168
00:13:03,760 --> 00:13:05,553
- We have clearance, Clarence.
- Roger, Roger.
-我们可以起飞了
-收到

169
00:13:05,762 --> 00:13:07,639
What's our vector, Victor?
伟达，航向指示是什么？

170
00:13:07,847 --> 00:13:11,976
<i>- I want radio clearance. Over.
- That's Clarence Oveur. Over.</i>
-我想要无线电指示
-我是欧家伦

171
00:13:12,268 --> 00:13:13,353
<i>- Roger.
- Huh?</i>
-收到
-什么？

172
00:13:13,603 --> 00:13:16,231
<i>- Roger. Over.
- Huh? Who?</i>
-收到？
-谁？

173
00:13:41,047 --> 00:13:43,132
Do you feel all right, sir?
先生，你没事吧？

174
00:13:43,424 --> 00:13:46,177
Oh, I haven't flown for a long time.
我很久没有乘搭飞机了

175
00:13:54,811 --> 00:13:56,938
Good evening.
This is Captain Oveur speaking.
各位好，我是欧机长

176
00:13:57,855 --> 00:14:00,108
<i>We'll be cruising
at 36,000 feet this evening...</i>
我们今晚会在
三万六千英尺上空飞行

177
00:14:00,358 --> 00:14:03,236
(男孩生活)

178
00:14:05,363 --> 00:14:09,576
(修女生活)

179
00:14:10,910 --> 00:14:12,870
<i>Relax and enjoy your flight.</i>
放松，好好享受今次旅程

180
00:14:13,121 --> 00:14:14,664
Would you like something to read?
想看点什么吗？

181
00:14:14,998 --> 00:14:17,250
Do you have anything light?
有没有轻松一些的？

182
00:14:18,793 --> 00:14:22,630
How about this leaflet,
"Famous Jewish Sports Legends"?
“著名犹太运动巨星”
册子如何？

183
00:14:22,880 --> 00:14:24,966
Yes. Thank you.
好的，劳驾

184
00:14:26,092 --> 00:14:29,012
- Ted! What are you doing here?
- I've got to talk to you.
-泰德，你为何会在这里？
-我得和你谈谈

185
00:14:29,220 --> 00:14:31,556
You shouldn't have come.
I don't have time now.
你不该上机，我现在没时间

186
00:14:31,848 --> 00:14:33,641
- Stewardess?
- Excuse me.
-小姐？
-失陪

187
00:14:46,946 --> 00:14:50,783
No wonder you're upset. She's lovely.
难怪你不开心，她很可爱

188
00:14:52,785 --> 00:14:55,413
And a darling figure.
身材又好

189
00:14:55,622 --> 00:14:59,834
Supple, pouting breasts, firm thighs.
肌肤充满弹性，丰乳纤腿

190
00:15:01,377 --> 00:15:04,297
It's a shame you two
don't get along.
可惜你俩合不来

191
00:15:04,589 --> 00:15:06,633
Yes, I know.
我知道

192
00:15:06,925 --> 00:15:09,344
Things used to be different.
以前并不是这样的

193
00:15:11,638 --> 00:15:14,140
I remember when we first met.
我记得我们首次相遇的情形

194
00:15:14,432 --> 00:15:16,935
It was during the war.
是战时的事

195
00:15:17,185 --> 00:15:21,773
I was in the air force, stationed in
Drambuie, off the Barbary Coast.
我加入空军
驻守巴巴利海岸的杜林比

196
00:15:23,066 --> 00:15:25,235
<i>I used to hang out
at the Magumba Bar.</i>
经常往马金巴酒吧

197
00:15:25,526 --> 00:15:28,571
<i>It was a rough place.
The seediest dive on the wharf,</i>
那是一处品流复杂的地方

198
00:15:28,780 --> 00:15:33,201
<i>populated with every reject and
cut-throat from Bombay to Calcutta.</i>
三山五岳的人都聚集在那儿

199
00:15:33,451 --> 00:15:35,620
<i>It was worse than Detroit.</i>
比底特律还要差

200
00:15:46,130 --> 00:15:48,132
<i>The mood in the place was ugly.</i>
那儿的气氛也不好

201
00:15:48,383 --> 00:15:51,052
<i>You wouldn't be there unless
you knew how to use your fists.</i>
拳头要够硬才可以往那里

202
00:15:51,302 --> 00:15:53,930
<i>A fight broke out almost every night.</i>
几乎每晚都会发生打斗

203
00:17:01,706 --> 00:17:05,585
<i>I didn't go there that night to fall in love.
I just wanted a couple of drinks.</i>
我并非往那里找情人
只想喝几杯

204
00:17:05,877 --> 00:17:07,587
<i>And suddenly, there she was.</i>
突然之间，我看到她

205
00:17:17,055 --> 00:17:20,850
<i>I was captivated, entranced.
It hit me like a thunderbolt.</i>
我完全被她俘虏，像遭电击

206
00:17:21,100 --> 00:17:24,979
<i>I had to ask this guy to pinch me
to make sure I wasn't dreaming.</i>
我得叫这厮捏我
以确保自己不是在做梦

207
00:17:29,901 --> 00:17:31,444
<i>I was afraid to approach her,</i>
我害怕上前认识她

208
00:17:31,736 --> 00:17:34,197
<i>but that night, fate was on my side.</i>
但那晚，我们注定相识

209
00:20:33,835 --> 00:20:37,088
<i>We laughed, we talked, we danced.</i>
我们谈天、说笑和跳舞

210
00:20:37,338 --> 00:20:40,758
I never wanted it to end.
I guess I still don't.
我不想那晚结束，现在亦然

211
00:20:40,967 --> 00:20:44,679
Enough about me. I hope
this hasn't been boring for you.
我说够了，希望没把你闷坏

212
00:20:44,929 --> 00:20:49,559
But whenever I talk about Elaine, I get
so carried away. I lose all track of time.
但每当说起绮莲，我都很投入
浑然忘记了时间

213
00:20:51,936 --> 00:20:53,688
Would you like to order dinner?
想要晚餐吗？

214
00:20:53,938 --> 00:20:58,067
- Joey will have steak. We'll have fish.
- When can I see the cockpit?
-祖儿吃牛扒，我们则吃鱼
-我何时可以参观驾驶舱？

215
00:20:58,401 --> 00:21:01,946
The pilots are probably too busy
flying the plane for that.
机师现在很忙

216
00:21:02,238 --> 00:21:03,364
Aw, gee whizz!
真气人！

217
00:21:03,573 --> 00:21:07,285
I'll talk to the captain
and see what I can arrange.
我跟机长说，且看能否安排

218
00:21:07,493 --> 00:21:09,621
Gee, that'd be swell!
太好了！

219
00:21:12,248 --> 00:21:14,167
Would you care to order your dinners?
想吃晚餐吗？

220
00:21:16,085 --> 00:21:17,670
我想吃牛扒

221
00:21:21,466 --> 00:21:23,259
我要鱼

222
00:21:30,808 --> 00:21:33,561
Excuse me, I happened to be passing.
我刚巧经过

223
00:21:33,811 --> 00:21:35,939
I thought you might like some coffee.
你要咖啡吗？

224
00:21:36,189 --> 00:21:38,650
That's very nice of you. Thank you.
你真有心，谢谢

225
00:21:41,110 --> 00:21:43,571
- Won't you sit down?
- Thank you.
-坐吧
-谢谢

226
00:21:46,699 --> 00:21:49,410
- Cream?
- No, I take it black.
-加奶吗？
-不，我喝黑咖啡的

227
00:21:49,744 --> 00:21:50,828
Like my men.
像我的男人一样

228
00:22:58,146 --> 00:23:01,190
Ted, I never knew
I could be so happy.
泰德，我实在太快乐了

229
00:23:01,441 --> 00:23:04,611
These past few months
have been wonderful.
这几个月简直是神仙生活

230
00:23:04,819 --> 00:23:08,448
Tomorrow, why don't we drive
to that little seafood place and...
不如明天我们去吃海鲜

231
00:23:09,782 --> 00:23:13,578
- What's the matter?
- My orders came through.
-怎么了？
-我接到命令

232
00:23:13,786 --> 00:23:15,455
My squadron ships out tomorrow.
我的部队要明天出发

233
00:23:15,663 --> 00:23:18,917
We're bombing the storage depots
at Daiquiri at 1800 hours.
我们要在六点钟
轰炸戴基利的补给站

234
00:23:19,167 --> 00:23:21,794
We're coming in from the north,
below their radar.
我们由北面进袭
低于他们的雷达

235
00:23:22,086 --> 00:23:26,299
- When will you be back?
- I can't tell you that. It's classified.
-你何时回来？
-我不能说，是机密

236
00:23:27,216 --> 00:23:30,970
Oh, Ted, please be careful.
I worry about you so much.
泰德，万事小心，我很担心

237
00:23:32,305 --> 00:23:33,431
I love you, Elaine.
我爱你，绮莲

238
00:23:33,765 --> 00:23:35,642
I love you.
我爱你

239
00:23:56,496 --> 00:24:00,041
<i>Flight 209er,
this is Denver flight control.</i>
209号班机，这是丹佛控制塔

240
00:24:00,333 --> 00:24:04,629
<i>You're approaching rough weather.
Please climb to 42,000 feet.</i>
前面天气并不稳定
请上升至四万二千英尺

241
00:24:05,755 --> 00:24:08,466
- Roger, Denver.
- We have a visitor.
-收到
-有访客到

242
00:24:08,800 --> 00:24:09,884
Hello.
你好

243
00:24:10,176 --> 00:24:13,930
Captain Oveur, Mr Murdock,
and Mr Basta, this is Joey Hammen.
欧机长、梅先生、白先生
这是夏祖儿

244
00:24:14,180 --> 00:24:16,057
- Hi, Joey.
- Come up here.
-祖儿，你好
-过来

245
00:24:16,307 --> 00:24:19,894
This is for special visitors.
Would you like to have it?
这是送给访客的，想要吗？

246
00:24:20,103 --> 00:24:24,315
- Thank you. Thanks a lot.
- Sure. Ever been in a cockpit?
-实在谢谢你
-别客气，到过驾驶舱没有？

247
00:24:24,607 --> 00:24:27,735
No, I've never been up
in a plane before.
没有，我从没乘搭过飞机

248
00:24:27,986 --> 00:24:29,988
Have you ever seen
a grown man naked?
你见过成年男性裸体吗？

249
00:24:30,238 --> 00:24:33,866
- Shall I check the weather?
- No, why don't you take care of it?
-该看看天气吗？
-不，你负责吧

250
00:24:34,200 --> 00:24:37,870
Joey, do you ever hang around
the gymnasium?
祖儿，你有否到过体操馆？

251
00:24:38,204 --> 00:24:41,541
- We'd better get back.
- No, Joey can stay for a while.
-我们还是回去吧
-不，祖儿可以多留一会

252
00:24:41,833 --> 00:24:43,835
- Could I?
- OK, if you don't get in the way.
-真的？
-只要你不碍事便行

253
00:24:44,085 --> 00:24:48,006
Flight 209er to Denver,
climbing to cruise at 42,000.
209号班机叫丹佛控制塔
我们升至四万二千英尺上空前进

254
00:24:48,298 --> 00:24:51,342
We'll report again over Lincoln.
Over and out.
我们到林肯上空时会再报到

255
00:24:51,593 --> 00:24:55,305
Wait a minute, I know you.
You're Kareem Abdul Jabbar.
慢着，我认得你，你是渣巴

256
00:24:55,555 --> 00:24:58,224
You play basketball
for the Los Angeles Lakers.
效力洛杉矶湖人队的

257
00:24:59,225 --> 00:25:01,603
Sorry, you have me confused
with someone else.
抱歉，你认错人了

258
00:25:01,853 --> 00:25:04,397
My name's Roger Murdock.
I'm the co-pilot.
我叫梅罗渣，是副机师

259
00:25:04,689 --> 00:25:09,068
You are Kareem! I've seen you play.
My dad's got season tickets.
你是渣巴，我看过你比赛
我爸买了季票

260
00:25:09,319 --> 00:25:11,946
You should go back to your seat now.
Right, Clarence?
你该返回座位，对吗？家伦

261
00:25:13,281 --> 00:25:15,992
No, he's not bothering anyone.
Let him stay here.
不，他没骚扰任何人
让他留下

262
00:25:17,493 --> 00:25:20,997
All right, but just remember
my name is Roger Murdock.
好，但记着，我叫做梅罗渣

263
00:25:21,247 --> 00:25:22,665
I'm an airline pilot.
是个机师

264
00:25:22,874 --> 00:25:24,417
I think you're the greatest,
我觉得你是最出色的球员

265
00:25:24,667 --> 00:25:29,047
but my dad says you don't work
hard enough on defence.
但爸说你在防守方面做得不够

266
00:25:29,339 --> 00:25:32,759
And he says lots of times
you don't even run downcourt.
他经常说你甚至不回防

267
00:25:33,009 --> 00:25:35,970
And you don't try,
except during the play-offs.
在季后赛时才偶尔回防

268
00:25:36,220 --> 00:25:37,847
The hell I don't!
我有回防的！

269
00:25:39,724 --> 00:25:43,186
Listen, kid, I've been hearing that crap
ever since I was at UCLA.
自从我在大学开始
已不断听到这种废话

270
00:25:43,436 --> 00:25:46,648
I'm out there busting my buns
every night.
我每晚都尽力比赛

271
00:25:46,898 --> 00:25:48,691
Tell your old man
to drag Walton and Lanier
叫你老爹把裁判员带来球场

272
00:25:49,025 --> 00:25:51,611
up and down the court for 48 minutes.
要他们上落跑48分钟吧

273
00:25:57,909 --> 00:26:01,120
Joey... Do you like movies
about gladiators?
祖儿
喜欢关于格斗者电影吗？

274
00:26:06,584 --> 00:26:09,462
Elaine, just hear me out.
绮莲，请听我说

275
00:26:09,671 --> 00:26:13,216
Things haven't been right
for a long time, but it'll be different,
我知道我们之间问题存在已久
但一切将有改变

276
00:26:13,466 --> 00:26:16,135
like in the beginning, remember?
就像开始时那样，记得吗？

277
00:26:16,386 --> 00:26:17,762
I remember everything.
我记得一切

278
00:26:19,514 --> 00:26:21,724
All I have is memories.
我只有回忆

279
00:26:21,975 --> 00:26:25,061
Mostly, I remember the nights
we were together.
记得最深刻的是晚上一起时

280
00:26:25,311 --> 00:26:28,439
I remember how you used to hold me,
我记得你怎样拥抱我

281
00:26:28,690 --> 00:26:31,651
how I used to sit on your face
and wriggle, and...
我怎样坐在你的面上摆动

282
00:26:31,901 --> 00:26:35,280
afterwards, how we'd watch
till the sun came up.
然后我们会一起看日出

283
00:26:35,572 --> 00:26:38,700
When it did, it was almost like...
当太阳升起时

284
00:26:38,992 --> 00:26:42,912
like each new day was created
only for us.
就像那新的一天是为我们而设

285
00:26:43,162 --> 00:26:45,748
That's the way
I've always wanted it to be.
我一直就想这样

286
00:26:45,957 --> 00:26:47,500
But it won't be.
可惜事与愿违

287
00:26:47,792 --> 00:26:50,837
Not as long as you insist
on living in the past!
你一直活在过去！

288
00:27:01,848 --> 00:27:03,850
<i>You're too low, Ted!</i>
泰德，你飞得太低了！

289
00:27:08,646 --> 00:27:11,649
(美军精神病院有戊醇)

290
00:27:12,775 --> 00:27:15,236
The mind plays tricks on you.
你的脑袋又愚弄你了

291
00:27:17,614 --> 00:27:20,617
He looks so happy today, doesn't he?
他今天看来很高兴吧

292
00:27:20,909 --> 00:27:23,453
You look so happy today.
你今天看来很高兴

293
00:27:23,703 --> 00:27:27,832
OK, Robert, slip them down.
This won't hurt much.
罗拔，放他们下来，不痛的

294
00:27:28,124 --> 00:27:30,585
You got a telegram
from headquarters today.
总部今天有电报给你

295
00:27:30,835 --> 00:27:32,128
Headquarters? What is it?
总部？什么来的？

296
00:27:32,337 --> 00:27:36,174
A big building where generals meet,
but that's not important.
即将军聚首的巨型建筑物
算了

297
00:27:36,507 --> 00:27:38,801
They've cleared you of any blame
for what happened on that raid.
那次突击的事，他们不怪责你

298
00:27:39,052 --> 00:27:41,930
- Isn't that good news?
- Is it?
-这岂非好消息？
-是吗？

299
00:27:43,181 --> 00:27:47,018
Because of my mistake,
six men didn't return from that raid.
由于我的过失，有六人死亡

300
00:27:47,310 --> 00:27:49,729
Seven. Lieutenant Zip
died this morning.
是七个，薛中尉今早逝世

301
00:27:50,939 --> 00:27:54,442
But Dr Sandler says you'll be out
in a week. Isn't that wonderful?
但沉医生说你一周后可以出院
这不是好消息吗？

302
00:27:56,027 --> 00:27:58,404
I wish I could say the same
for George Zip.
但愿我能这样跟薛佐治说

303
00:27:59,239 --> 00:28:03,201
Be patient, Ted. Nobody expects you
to get over this immediately.
耐心一点吧！
没有人预期你会立即忘记此事

304
00:28:03,493 --> 00:28:06,496
Hey, Striker, how about a break?
I'm getting tired.
史，可否歇一歇？我很累

305
00:28:07,622 --> 00:28:09,249
Yeah, all right. Take five.
好的，休息五分钟吧

306
00:28:11,042 --> 00:28:12,293
Thanks.
谢谢你

307
00:28:13,002 --> 00:28:17,799
I found a wonderful apartment for us.
It has a brick fireplace
我为我们找到新房子
有砖造的火炉

308
00:28:18,049 --> 00:28:21,678
and a cute bedroom
with mirrors on the ceiling and...
睡房也很特别，天花板有镜子

309
00:28:21,928 --> 00:28:23,888
Red Leader, I'm going down!
红队长，我要下去了！

310
00:28:24,180 --> 00:28:28,309
Captain Geline. He thinks he's a pilot,
still fighting the war.
姬上尉以为自己是机师
仍在打仗

311
00:28:29,978 --> 00:28:32,522
I've found the tunnel, Johnson!
It's this way!
我找到隧道了，这边

312
00:28:32,814 --> 00:28:35,358
$25 for a cigarette is too much!
二十五元一根烟太贵了！

313
00:28:39,112 --> 00:28:42,198
- What's his problem?
- It's Lieutenant Hurwitz.
-他怎么了？
-他是胡中尉

314
00:28:42,407 --> 00:28:45,952
Severe shell shock.
He thinks he's Ethel Merman.
严重弹震症
以为自己是雄性人鱼

315
00:29:04,304 --> 00:29:06,264
War is hell.
战争实在可怕

316
00:29:10,727 --> 00:29:14,939
Excuse me, sir. Would you like
some coffee before dinner?
先生，吃晚餐前想喝杯咖啡吗

317
00:29:15,231 --> 00:29:17,108
No. No, thank you.
不用了，谢谢

318
00:29:18,818 --> 00:29:22,447
- Would you like another cup?
- I will, but Jim won't.
-要多一杯吗？
-好的，但占不要了

319
00:29:22,739 --> 00:29:25,408
I think I will have
another cup of coffee.
我想要多杯咖啡

320
00:29:27,035 --> 00:29:29,871
<i>Jim never has a second
cup of coffee at home.</i>
占在家从来不会多要一杯咖啡

321
00:29:35,710 --> 00:29:38,087
- Excuse me, Sister.
- Yes?
-修女
-什么事？

322
00:29:38,379 --> 00:29:43,718
- There's a little girl on board who's ill.
- Oh, yes, I saw. Poor child.
-机上有一名病重的小女孩
-她真可怜

323
00:29:43,968 --> 00:29:46,846
Could I borrow your guitar?
I thought I'd cheer her up.
我想借你的结他去令她开心点

324
00:29:47,055 --> 00:29:49,307
- Of course.
- Thank you.
-好的
-谢谢你

325
00:29:56,272 --> 00:29:58,024
- Hi.
- Hi.
-你好
-你好

326
00:29:58,316 --> 00:30:00,485
Do you mind if I talk
to your daughter?
我可否跟你女儿谈谈？

327
00:30:00,693 --> 00:30:02,987
I think that'd be nice.
随便

328
00:30:05,323 --> 00:30:09,410
- Hi, I'm Randy.
- I'm Lisa. Oh, you have a guitar!
-你好，我叫兰迪
-我是莉莎，你有结他

329
00:30:10,870 --> 00:30:13,414
I thought maybe you'd
like to hear a song.
想听歌吗？

330
00:30:13,665 --> 00:30:15,083
I'd love to.
好！

331
00:30:15,291 --> 00:30:18,127
OK. Let's see...
让我想想

332
00:30:18,336 --> 00:30:20,755
This is one of my favorites.
这是我最喜欢的

333
00:31:43,922 --> 00:31:45,423
You're late. We've been waiting.
你迟到，我们在等你

334
00:31:45,632 --> 00:31:47,634
- Who's first?
- Go ahead, Clarence.
-谁先？
-你来吧！家伦

335
00:31:47,926 --> 00:31:49,427
How's the weather?
天气怎样？

336
00:31:49,719 --> 00:31:53,806
We got some heavy stuff ahead of us.
We've got to climb on top.
前面有厚云层，要上升飞行

337
00:31:55,642 --> 00:32:00,480
Yeah, after the war, I wanted
to get as far away as possible,
战后我想尽量离开伤心地

338
00:32:00,730 --> 00:32:03,650
so Elaine and I
joined the Peace Corps.
故我和绮莲加入和平大使计划

339
00:32:03,900 --> 00:32:06,986
We were assigned
to an isolated tribe, the Molombos.
我们被派往接触偏远部族
莫林保人

340
00:32:08,488 --> 00:32:10,907
They'd never seen Americans before.
他们从没见过美国人

341
00:32:24,128 --> 00:32:28,466
<i>It was really a challenge, introducing
them to our Western culture.</i>
向他们介绍西方文化
是一个大挑战

342
00:32:33,346 --> 00:32:35,223
<i>At first, they didn't know
what to think of us.</i>
起初，他们对我们有戒心

343
00:32:35,473 --> 00:32:37,684
<i>But soon, we gained their trust.</i>
但很快我们获得他们信任

344
00:32:46,484 --> 00:32:49,320
It'll help you better
prepare storing foods
这样保存食物更好

345
00:32:49,529 --> 00:32:52,699
for the up and coming
monsoon months.
可保留至季候风月份

346
00:32:52,991 --> 00:32:57,453
Also, Supperware products
are ideal for storing leftovers
这些用来存放吃剩的东西最好

347
00:32:57,704 --> 00:33:00,498
to help stretch your food dollar.
价廉物美

348
00:33:00,748 --> 00:33:04,002
This two-quart
"Seals-M-Rite" container
这个保鲜盒

349
00:33:04,252 --> 00:33:06,963
keeps hot dog buns fresh for days.
可以令热狗包保持新鲜多天

350
00:33:07,255 --> 00:33:11,259
<i>These people had been completely
isolated from civilization.</i>
这些人一直与文明隔绝

351
00:33:12,385 --> 00:33:14,721
<i>No one had outlined a physical
fitness program for them,</i>
从没有人替他们制订保健计划

352
00:33:15,013 --> 00:33:16,806
<i>and they had no athletic equipment.</i>
他们亦没有运动器材

353
00:33:17,056 --> 00:33:20,560
<i>I started them on simple calisthenics,
worked up to rudimentary game skills,</i>
我教他们做柔软体操
和一些基本球技

354
00:33:20,810 --> 00:33:23,479
<i>and finally,
advanced competitive theory.</i>
最后令他们有竞赛能力

355
00:33:24,397 --> 00:33:26,691
<i>I was patient,
and they were eager to learn.</i>
我很有耐性，他们亦很好学

356
00:33:26,983 --> 00:33:29,068
<i>They seemed to enjoy themselves.</i>
他们似乎玩得很开心

357
00:33:29,319 --> 00:33:31,738
<i>Probably due to advanced
American teaching techniques,</i>
大概因为有先进的美国教法

358
00:33:31,946 --> 00:33:34,365
<i>we bridged the generations
of isolation,</i>
他们再不与世隔绝

359
00:33:34,657 --> 00:33:37,785
<i>and communicated successfully
with the Molombos.</i>
我们成功与莫林保人沟通

360
00:33:43,875 --> 00:33:47,378
They're getting the hang of it. When we
re-enlist, I'll teach them baseball.
他们已把握到个中精髓
再来时，我会教他们打棒球

361
00:33:48,171 --> 00:33:50,340
Ted, I don't want to stay here.
泰德，我不想留在这里

362
00:33:50,590 --> 00:33:54,510
It's time to go home to the plans
we made before the war.
该回家实行战前定下的计划

363
00:33:56,763 --> 00:34:00,433
A lot of people made plans
before the war. Like George Zip.
很多人在战前都有很多计划
薛佐治就是其中一分子

364
00:34:05,563 --> 00:34:10,109
<i>At that moment, I realised Elaine
had doubts about our relationship.</i>
那刻我知道绮莲对我们的
关系有疑问

365
00:34:10,360 --> 00:34:13,655
<i>And that, as much as anything else,
led to my drinking problem.</i>
这引起我的饮水问题

366
00:34:15,281 --> 00:34:19,077
We did come back to the States.
I tried a number of jobs.
我们返美，我做过很多工作

367
00:34:19,410 --> 00:34:22,413
I could go on,
but I'd probably bore you.
我可以继续说，但你会闷坏

368
00:34:22,664 --> 00:34:25,166
I really couldn't blame Elaine.
She wanted a career.
实在不能怪责绮莲
她想有自己的事业

369
00:34:32,048 --> 00:34:34,509
- I can't stand it.
- What is it?
-我受不了
-什么事？

370
00:34:34,759 --> 00:34:36,594
- Yes?
- It's my stomach.
-什么事？
-我的胃很不舒服

371
00:34:37,971 --> 00:34:40,848
I haven't felt this awful since we saw
that Ronald Reagan film.
自从看过列根那电影后
我从没试过那么不舒服

372
00:34:41,641 --> 00:34:44,602
I'll see if I can find some Dramamine.
且看我能否找到晕机药

373
00:34:51,859 --> 00:34:54,404
Captain, a woman passenger
is very sick.
机长，有一名女乘客很不舒服

374
00:34:55,405 --> 00:34:58,616
<i>- Airsick?
- I think so, I've never seen it so acute.</i>
-晕机？
-不是，她真的很辛苦

375
00:35:00,243 --> 00:35:03,871
Find out if there's a doctor on board,
as quietly as you can.
悄悄地找找机上有没有医生

376
00:35:06,874 --> 00:35:11,129
Joey, have you ever been
in a Turkish prison?
祖儿，你到过土耳其监狱吗？

377
00:35:13,506 --> 00:35:16,342
I shouldn't have had
that second cup of coffee.
我不该喝第二杯咖啡

378
00:35:27,186 --> 00:35:29,522
<i>Jim never vomits at home.</i>
占在家从不呕吐

379
00:35:30,398 --> 00:35:34,694
Sorry to wake you. I'm looking for a
doctor. There's nothing to worry about.
抱歉弄醒你，但我想找医生

380
00:35:34,944 --> 00:35:38,573
Stewardess, I think
the man next to me is a doctor.
小姐，我身旁的该是医生

381
00:35:38,823 --> 00:35:42,452
Sir, excuse me. Sorry to wake you,
are you a doctor?
先生，抱歉弄醒你
但你是医生吗？

382
00:35:42,744 --> 00:35:45,371
- That's right.
- We have sick passengers.
-是的
-我们有乘客不舒服

383
00:35:45,663 --> 00:35:48,708
- Could you take a look at them?
- Yes, of course.
-可否去看看他们？
-好的

384
00:35:58,092 --> 00:36:00,303
Let me see your tongue.
让我看看你的舌头

385
00:36:29,040 --> 00:36:31,167
I'll be back in a minute.
我很快回来

386
00:36:36,047 --> 00:36:39,968
Tell the captain to land.
She must go to a hospital.
叫机长降落，要送她往医院

387
00:36:40,260 --> 00:36:41,886
A hospital! What is it?
医院！什么？

388
00:36:42,136 --> 00:36:44,681
It's a big building with patients,
but that's not important.
是一座有病人的建筑物，算了

389
00:36:44,889 --> 00:36:47,559
- I must speak to the captain.
- Certainly.
-我得跟机长谈谈
-好的

390
00:36:54,482 --> 00:36:56,442
Victor, we're running into heavy...
伟达，我们遇上浓…

391
00:36:57,026 --> 00:36:58,820
Roger, take over!
罗渣，快接手！

392
00:37:20,508 --> 00:37:23,720
- Captain, how soon can you land?
- I can't tell.
-机长，何时可以降落？
-我不知道

393
00:37:23,970 --> 00:37:26,764
- You can tell me. I'm a doctor.
- No, I'm not sure.
-你该知道的，我是医生
-不，我不清楚

394
00:37:27,015 --> 00:37:31,561
- Can't you take a guess?
- Not for another two hours.
-可否猜一猜？
-起码两小时之后吧

395
00:37:31,811 --> 00:37:33,688
You can't take a guess
for another two hours?
你要在两小时后才去猜一猜？

396
00:37:33,980 --> 00:37:37,775
No, we can't land.
Fog has closed down everything.
我们无法降落，太大雾了

397
00:37:37,984 --> 00:37:40,069
We've got to get through to Chicago.
我们得尽快降落

398
00:37:47,410 --> 00:37:49,662
Get him out of there!
带他走

399
00:38:13,895 --> 00:38:16,606
- What is it, Doctor? What's going on?
- I'm not sure.
-医生，究竟发生什么事？
-我不清楚

400
00:38:16,856 --> 00:38:20,193
Haven't seen anything like this
since the Anita Bryant concert.
自拜恩的演唱会后
从未见过这种事

401
00:38:20,526 --> 00:38:24,739
- What did we have for dinner?
- We had a choice - steak or fish.
-我们晚餐吃什么？
-可以选牛扒或鱼

402
00:38:25,531 --> 00:38:27,575
Yes, I remember. I had lasagna.
我记得，我吃烤宽面条

403
00:38:27,867 --> 00:38:30,036
- What did he have?
- He had fish.
-他吃了什么？
-吃了鱼

404
00:38:30,328 --> 00:38:33,957
Doctor, two more are sick.
The other passengers are worried.
医生，又有两人不舒服
乘客都很担心

405
00:38:34,249 --> 00:38:36,167
I'll handle the passengers.
我会处理

406
00:38:36,459 --> 00:38:40,964
Find out what the sick people had for
dinner. This is Captain Oveur speaking.
找出病人晚餐吃过什么
我是欧机长

407
00:38:41,214 --> 00:38:44,467
<i>It's bumpy, but we'll be past it
in a few minutes.</i>
我们遇上气流但很快会没事

408
00:38:44,717 --> 00:38:48,304
<i>We're now flying over Hoover Dam,</i>
我们正飞越胡佛水霸

409
00:38:48,555 --> 00:38:51,432
<i>and later we'll pass
south of the Grand Canyon.</i>
跟着我们会飞越大峡谷

410
00:38:51,766 --> 00:38:54,269
<i>Meanwhile, relax
and enjoy your flight, OK?</i>
与此同时，请放松
好好享受今次旅程

411
00:38:56,187 --> 00:39:00,108
Chicago, this is flight 209er.
We're in trouble.
芝加哥，这是209号班机
我们有麻烦

412
00:39:00,400 --> 00:39:03,945
Have all traffic below us cleared.
I want a priority landing in Chicago.
请给我们优先降落权

413
00:39:08,741 --> 00:39:09,993
Yes?
什么事？

414
00:39:10,285 --> 00:39:12,620
My husband's very sick.
Can you do something?
我的丈夫很不舒服，请帮忙

415
00:39:12,912 --> 00:39:16,291
The doctor will be with you
in just a moment.
医生很快会来

416
00:39:16,541 --> 00:39:20,795
- Do you know what he had for dinner?
- Yes, we both had fish. Why?
-知否他晚餐吃了什么？
-我们都吃了鱼，为什么？

417
00:39:21,045 --> 00:39:25,258
It's nothing to be alarmed about.
We'll be back to you very quickly.
没什么，我们很快回来

418
00:39:31,931 --> 00:39:33,892
Doctor, Mr Hammen ate fish,
医生，夏先生吃了鱼

419
00:39:34,100 --> 00:39:37,437
and Randy said there are five
more cases, and they all had fish.
兰迪说又有五人不舒服
他们全都吃过鱼

420
00:39:37,770 --> 00:39:41,065
The co-pilot had fish.
What did the navigator have?
副机师也吃了鱼
导航员吃过什么？

421
00:39:41,316 --> 00:39:42,650
He had fish.
也是吃过鱼

422
00:39:42,901 --> 00:39:45,403
All right, now we know
what we're up against.
好，现在知道什么一回事了

423
00:39:45,695 --> 00:39:50,867
Every passenger who had fish for
dinner will soon become violently ill.
吃过鱼的人都十分不适

424
00:39:51,117 --> 00:39:54,787
- Just how serious is it?
- Extremely serious.
-有多严重？
-极之严重

425
00:39:55,079 --> 00:39:58,207
It starts with a slight fever,
dryness of the throat.
首先会些微发烧，喉咙干涸

426
00:39:58,499 --> 00:40:01,502
When the virus penetrates,
the victim becomes dizzy,
当病毒进一步入侵
病人会觉得晕眩

427
00:40:01,794 --> 00:40:04,005
and begins to experience
an itching rash.
感到浑身痕痒

428
00:40:04,255 --> 00:40:06,758
From there, the poison works
on the central nervous system,
跟着病毒会入侵中央神经系统

429
00:40:07,050 --> 00:40:11,179
causing severe muscle spasms,
followed by the inevitable drooling.
令肌肉严重抽筋
不能自控地流口水

430
00:40:11,429 --> 00:40:13,973
At this point,
the digestive system collapses,
这时消化系统会完全崩溃

431
00:40:14,224 --> 00:40:16,643
accompanied
by uncontrollable flatulence.
肠胃气胀

432
00:40:16,851 --> 00:40:21,481
Until the poor bastard is reduced to
a quivering, wasted piece of jelly.
之后那病人会浑身乏力
有如一堆果冻

433
00:40:30,949 --> 00:40:33,284
(第11行至21行
第13行至51行)

434
00:40:39,540 --> 00:40:42,335
Put it on... automatic pilot.
开启…自动机师

435
00:40:43,711 --> 00:40:47,048
Automatic pilot, automatic pilot...
There it is!
自动机师…在这里了！

436
00:40:55,723 --> 00:40:58,101
I'll go back to the passengers.
我去看看乘客如何

437
00:41:00,353 --> 00:41:02,814
<i>Come in, 209er. This is Chicago.</i>
209号班机，请回答

438
00:41:03,106 --> 00:41:06,192
<i>Flight 209er, come in.</i>
209号班机，请回答

439
00:41:06,484 --> 00:41:08,695
This is Elaine Dickinson,
the stewardess.
我是空中小姐狄绮莲

440
00:41:08,945 --> 00:41:12,615
Captain Oveur's passed out. We've
lost the co-pilot and navigator, too.
欧机长昏倒了
副机师和导航员亦然

441
00:41:12,865 --> 00:41:14,784
<i>- We're in trouble.
- Roger.</i>
-我们有麻烦
-收到

442
00:41:15,034 --> 00:41:17,328
<i>I'm Steve McCroskey,
Chicago air control.</i>
我是芝加哥航空署的麦斯堤

443
00:41:17,620 --> 00:41:21,207
I'll be back in a minute.
Hold all takeoffs.
我很快会跟你再联络
暂停所有航机起飞

444
00:41:21,457 --> 00:41:23,668
When 508 reports, bring it straight in.
508会报时，立即接进来

445
00:41:23,918 --> 00:41:27,338
Suspend all meal service
on flights out of Los Angeles.
暂停由洛杉矶起程的
航机的三餐供应

446
00:41:27,589 --> 00:41:30,300
Tell all dispatchers
to remain at their posts.
叫所有调度员留在岗位

447
00:41:30,550 --> 00:41:32,010
- How about coffee?
- No, thanks.
-喝杯咖啡吗？
-不用了，谢谢

448
00:41:32,302 --> 00:41:35,513
I want the weather
on every available landing field.
我要所有可能降落地点的
天气报告

449
00:41:35,763 --> 00:41:37,181
You understand?
懂吗？

450
00:41:37,390 --> 00:41:40,351
Any place available
to land that plane!
有没有可以降落的地方？

451
00:41:40,602 --> 00:41:43,938
Go to the tower
and get a runway diagram.
往控制塔，找来跑道图

452
00:41:44,230 --> 00:41:47,191
Check down the field
for emergency equipment.
找来紧急事故器材

453
00:41:47,442 --> 00:41:51,404
Chief, we got fog every place
east of the Rockies.
洛杉矶以东所有地方都有雾

454
00:41:51,654 --> 00:41:54,282
They'll have
to come through to Chicago.
他们得来芝加哥降落

455
00:41:55,408 --> 00:41:57,827
Looks like I picked the wrong week
to quit smoking.
似乎我不该在这星期戒烟

456
00:41:58,119 --> 00:42:02,874
Get the best available man
who won't crack under pressure.
找泰山崩于前而不动声色的人

457
00:42:03,124 --> 00:42:05,168
How about Mr Rogers?
罗先生如何？

458
00:42:08,421 --> 00:42:10,340
Get me Rex Kramer.
找祈力斯来

459
00:42:15,120 --> 00:42:18,720
<i>Next to the throttle
is the airspeed gauge.</i>
在节流杆旁的便是速度计

460
00:42:19,000 --> 00:42:21,680
<i>What speed does it indicate?</i>
现在是什么速度？

461
00:42:22,520 --> 00:42:24,560
520 miles per hour.
每小时520哩

462
00:42:24,840 --> 00:42:28,480
Good. Very good.
Now, check your altitude.
好，很好，现在查看高度

463
00:42:28,760 --> 00:42:32,240
That's the dial below and right
of the airspeed indicator.
即是速度计右下方的针盘

464
00:42:33,280 --> 00:42:35,560
35,000 feet.
三万五千英尺

465
00:42:35,800 --> 00:42:38,160
No, wait. 34,000 feet.
不，慢着，三万四千英尺

466
00:42:38,440 --> 00:42:42,240
No. It's dropping!
It's dropping fast!
不，不断下降，下降得很快

467
00:42:42,520 --> 00:42:44,280
Why is it doing that?
为何这样？

468
00:42:46,680 --> 00:42:50,560
Oh, my God! The automatic pilot,
it's deflating!
天啊！自动机师正在泄气

469
00:42:50,800 --> 00:42:53,040
Elaine, don't panic.
绮莲，别恐慌

470
00:42:53,320 --> 00:42:55,840
On his belt line
there's a hollow tube.
它的腰带有一支管

471
00:42:56,080 --> 00:43:00,920
<i>That's the manual inflation nozzle.
Pull it out and blow on it.</i>
是吹气孔，拔它出来吹气吧！

472
00:43:04,680 --> 00:43:06,800
What the hell's going on up there?
究竟发生什么事？

473
00:44:00,160 --> 00:44:02,720
- Elaine.
- Yes, Doctor.
-绮莲
-是，医生

474
00:44:04,840 --> 00:44:06,480
You're a member of this crew.
你是这航机的一员

475
00:44:06,760 --> 00:44:09,400
- Can you face some unpleasant facts?
- No.
-能否接受可怕事实？
-不能

476
00:44:09,680 --> 00:44:12,840
Unless we hospitalise
those people quickly,
除非赶快送这些人往医院

477
00:44:13,120 --> 00:44:15,800
I can't be sure of saving their lives.
否则我不知道能否救他们

478
00:44:16,040 --> 00:44:19,360
Is there anyone on board
who can land this plane?
机上有没有人可以令飞机降落

479
00:44:23,240 --> 00:44:24,880
No one I know of.
据我所知就没有

480
00:44:25,680 --> 00:44:30,600
You ought to know our chances.
Our lives depend on just one thing -
该明白航机上
所有人的生死存亡

481
00:44:30,880 --> 00:44:35,280
finding someone to fly this plane
who didn't have fish for dinner.
取决于可以找到一个懂驾飞机
又没有吃过鱼的人

482
00:44:46,720 --> 00:44:49,960
Ladies and gentlemen,
this is your stewardess speaking.
各位，我是空中小姐

483
00:44:50,200 --> 00:44:54,080
We regret any inconvenience
the sudden cabin movement caused.
刚才机舱震动，对不起

484
00:44:54,320 --> 00:44:57,360
<i>This is due to periodic air pockets.</i>
这是因为遇上气流

485
00:44:57,640 --> 00:45:02,160
<i>There's no reason to become alarmed.
We hope you enjoy your flight.</i>
请别担心，好好享受旅程

486
00:45:03,320 --> 00:45:06,880
By the way, is there anyone on board
who can fly a plane?
此外，有没有人懂驾驶飞机？

487
00:45:35,880 --> 00:45:38,400
Hello. I'm Paul Carey from the airline.
I'm here to pick up Captain Kramer.
我是航空公司的贾保罗
是来接祈上尉的

488
00:45:38,640 --> 00:45:41,840
Yes. Come in, Paul.
Rex will be right out.
请进，力斯很快会出来

489
00:45:44,360 --> 00:45:46,560
Shep, sit. Sit!
羊羊，坐下！

490
00:45:46,800 --> 00:45:49,240
I understand there's an emergency.
我知道这是急事

491
00:45:50,000 --> 00:45:54,200
Something like that. There wasn't time
to tell me very much...
诸如此类，我也不大清楚

492
00:45:56,160 --> 00:45:57,880
Shep, no!
羊羊，不要！

493
00:45:58,160 --> 00:46:01,000
I'll bet exciting things happen
all the time down there.
你们经常遇上刺激的事吧

494
00:46:01,320 --> 00:46:03,880
The airline business
does have its moments.
航空事业确有其精彩时刻

495
00:46:04,160 --> 00:46:06,280
After a while, you get used to it.
稍后你自会适应

496
00:46:08,080 --> 00:46:09,680
Shep! Come!
羊羊，来！

497
00:46:11,280 --> 00:46:14,560
He gets so excited
when new people are here.
有新访客来到，它就很兴奋

498
00:46:14,840 --> 00:46:17,520
- Are you a pilot?
- No, I'm in...
-你是机师吗？
-不是，我…

499
00:46:18,240 --> 00:46:19,800
a training program.
正接受训练

500
00:46:20,080 --> 00:46:23,560
It's unbelievable.
It's just unbelievable.
难以置信

501
00:46:23,840 --> 00:46:26,160
How many times have I warned
about food inspection?
已警告过你多少遍要检查食物

502
00:46:26,400 --> 00:46:29,880
You'd think
someone would listen to you.
还以为有人会听你说

503
00:46:30,160 --> 00:46:33,200
Well, airport management,
the FAA, and the airlines...
机场管理层、飞管局
和航空公司…

504
00:46:34,520 --> 00:46:36,320
they're all cheats and liars.
他们都是骗子

505
00:46:36,600 --> 00:46:38,880
All right. Let's get out of here.
好，走吧

506
00:46:45,920 --> 00:46:50,280
I'm sorry, I was just looking
for someone with flying experience.
抱歉，我想找懂驾驶飞机的人

507
00:46:50,560 --> 00:46:53,520
When they built those roads,
they didn't think about drainage,
他们筑路时，没考虑去水问题

508
00:46:53,800 --> 00:46:58,320
so we had to take a special jeep
up to the main road.
故我们要乘特制吉普车往大路

509
00:46:58,600 --> 00:47:02,160
We were lucky to get a jeep,
since, just the day before,
很幸运我们找来吉普车

510
00:47:02,440 --> 00:47:05,760
the only one we had broke down.
It had a bad axle...
之前一天
我们那辆吉普车坏了

511
00:47:06,000 --> 00:47:08,920
Excuse me, sir.
There's a problem in the cockpit.
先生，驾驶舱有些问题

512
00:47:09,200 --> 00:47:10,760
The cockpit? What is it?
驾驶舱？什么？

513
00:47:11,000 --> 00:47:14,400
The little room where the pilot sits.
That's not important.
即机师坐的小房子，算了

514
00:47:14,640 --> 00:47:18,960
The first officer is ill. The captain needs
someone to help him with the radio.
副机师病倒了
机长想找人帮忙

515
00:47:19,280 --> 00:47:21,840
Do you know anything about planes?
你对飞机有认识吗？

516
00:47:22,120 --> 00:47:24,800
I flew in the war years ago.
多年前我在战时驾驶战机

517
00:47:25,800 --> 00:47:29,960
- I wouldn't know anything about it.
- Would you go up, please?
-我不懂得驾驶飞机
-可否跟我来？拜托

518
00:47:46,200 --> 00:47:48,520
The stewardess said...
那空姐说…

519
00:47:49,800 --> 00:47:53,200
- Both pilots?
- Can you fly this plane and land it?
-两名机师？
-你能否令这飞机降落？

520
00:47:54,360 --> 00:47:58,280
- Surely, you can't be serious.
- I am serious, and don't call me Shirley.
-你说笑吧？
-我是认真的，请别推辞

521
00:47:59,560 --> 00:48:03,000
Doctor, I've checked everyone.
Mr Striker's the only one.
医生，我问过所有人
只有史先生合适

522
00:48:03,280 --> 00:48:07,000
- What's your flying experience?
- I flew single-engine fighters.
-你有什么飞行经验？
-我驾驶过单引擎战机

523
00:48:07,280 --> 00:48:11,720
This plane has four engines.
It's an entirely different kind of flying.
这飞机有四个引擎
是截然不同的飞行经验

524
00:48:12,720 --> 00:48:15,000
It's an entirely different
kind of flying.
是截然不同的飞行经验

525
00:48:17,560 --> 00:48:20,040
I haven't touched
any kind of plane in six years.
我已有六年没接触任何飞机

526
00:48:20,280 --> 00:48:23,520
Mr Striker,
I know nothing about flying.
史先生，我并不懂得驾驶飞机

527
00:48:23,800 --> 00:48:28,680
But I do know that you're the only one
on this plane who can possibly fly it.
但我知道你是飞机上
唯一可能驾驶它的人

528
00:48:28,960 --> 00:48:30,760
You're the only chance we've got.
你是我们唯一的希望

529
00:49:10,120 --> 00:49:13,840
That's right. That's what I said.
You heard me.
对，我也这样说

530
00:49:14,160 --> 00:49:16,080
Tell Omaha to acknowledge
and stand by.
叫奥马哈准备

531
00:49:16,320 --> 00:49:19,760
Every piece of emergency equipment
you can reach.
找来一切应急工具

532
00:49:20,040 --> 00:49:22,200
Alert every rescue unit
from here to the Rockies.
通知由这里至洛矶山的
所有拯救单位

533
00:49:22,440 --> 00:49:24,240
Chief!
首领！

534
00:49:24,520 --> 00:49:28,160
- We'll need a free-landing flight check.
- It's your wife.
-我们要检查自动降落航机
-是你的太太

535
00:49:28,480 --> 00:49:31,480
I want the kids in bed by nine, the dog
fed, the yard watered, the gate locked.
我要孩子九时上床、喂好狗儿
替院子洒水、锁上大闸

536
00:49:31,760 --> 00:49:34,200
Get a note to the milkman -
"No more cheese."
给送牛奶人便条，不再要芝士

537
00:49:36,840 --> 00:49:38,720
Where the hell is Kramer?
祈力斯呢？

538
00:49:46,920 --> 00:49:50,600
No, he can't do that.
The risk of a flame-out's too great.
不，他做不来，起火机会太大

539
00:49:50,880 --> 00:49:53,760
Keep him at 24,000... No, feet.
要他保持在二万四千英尺高

540
00:49:57,520 --> 00:49:59,480
A passenger is
going to land that plane.
一名乘客打算令航机降落

541
00:49:59,720 --> 00:50:02,680
- Is that possible?
- It's a hundred to one shot.
-有可能吗？
-机会微乎其微

542
00:50:06,640 --> 00:50:09,960
- I know this guy.
- You do? Who is it?
-我认识这人
-真的？他是何方神圣？

543
00:50:10,240 --> 00:50:15,120
Ted Striker. I flew with him during
the war. It won't make my job easier.
史泰德，我在战时曾与他合作
但他越帮越忙

544
00:50:16,640 --> 00:50:19,960
Ted Striker was a crack
flight leader, up to a point.
史泰德是个不济飞行小组队长

545
00:50:20,240 --> 00:50:24,840
He was one of those men who...
felt too much inside.
他是那种…太感性的人

546
00:50:25,080 --> 00:50:26,880
Maybe you know that kind.
或许你也认识那种人

547
00:50:27,160 --> 00:50:30,360
He went all to pieces
on a particular mission.
有一次任务，他一败涂地

548
00:50:31,080 --> 00:50:33,680
Let's just hope
that doesn't happen tonight.
希望今晚不会这样

549
00:50:40,960 --> 00:50:44,840
Let's see... Altitude, 24,000 feet.
让我看看…高度，二万四千英尺

550
00:50:45,880 --> 00:50:49,360
Level flight. Speed, 520 knots.
保持这高度，速度520

551
00:50:50,120 --> 00:50:52,160
Course Zero Niner Zero.
航道090

552
00:50:52,400 --> 00:50:55,920
Trim, mixture.
Wash, soap, rinse, spin.
切条、搅均
洗净、冲水、摇干

553
00:50:59,400 --> 00:51:03,360
Ted! What are you doing here?
You can't fly this plane!
泰德，你在此做什么？
你不能驾驶这飞机！

554
00:51:03,640 --> 00:51:05,520
That's what I'm trying to tell them.
我正努力告诉他们这一点

555
00:51:05,800 --> 00:51:09,800
Elaine. I don't have time to be gentle,
so I'll be very direct.
绮莲，我没时间转弯抹角
得直接对你说

556
00:51:10,040 --> 00:51:12,480
Everyone is in a desperate situation.
大家的情况都很危险

557
00:51:12,800 --> 00:51:15,160
Mr Striker is the only hope we got.
史先生是我们唯一的希望

558
00:51:19,760 --> 00:51:22,800
Those are the flaps.
This is the thrust.
那些是襟翼，这是推力

559
00:51:24,160 --> 00:51:26,640
This must turn on the landing lights.
这会亮起降落灯

560
00:51:33,040 --> 00:51:36,840
(返回座位)

561
00:51:40,040 --> 00:51:43,920
- Mayday! Mayday!
- Mayday? What the hell is that?
-救命！…
-五月？怎么了？

562
00:51:44,200 --> 00:51:47,440
May Day's the Russian new year.
We'll have a big parade and serve...
五月是俄罗斯的新年
我们有大巡游

563
00:51:58,200 --> 00:52:00,480
I can't stand it any more.
我不能再忍受了

564
00:52:00,680 --> 00:52:03,040
I've got to get out of here!
我要出去！

565
00:52:03,320 --> 00:52:07,360
- Calm down! Get ahold of yourself!
- Please let me handle this.
-冷静！控制自己
-让我来吧

566
00:52:09,760 --> 00:52:12,840
Calm down. Get back to your seat.
I'll take care of this.
冷静，返回座位，我会处理

567
00:52:13,120 --> 00:52:14,920
Calm down. Get ahold of yourself.
冷静，控制自己

568
00:52:15,160 --> 00:52:17,320
Doctor, you're wanted on the phone.
医生，有人找你

569
00:52:17,560 --> 00:52:22,360
- Everything will be all right.
- Sister, I can handle this.
-一切会没事的
-修女，让我来

570
00:52:22,640 --> 00:52:24,680
Got to get out of here!
走开！

571
00:52:28,120 --> 00:52:30,440
We'd like you to have this flower.
我们想你收下这朵花

572
00:52:32,160 --> 00:52:34,200
Excuse me, sir, would you...
先生，你可否…

573
00:52:34,480 --> 00:52:36,680
Donations for Reverend Moon?
向蒙牧师捐献？

574
00:52:37,440 --> 00:52:38,640
Jews for Jesus?
犹太耶稣？

575
00:52:38,920 --> 00:52:40,760
Read about Jehovah's Witnesses?
耶和华证人？

576
00:52:42,000 --> 00:52:44,320
How about Buddhism?
佛教又如何？

577
00:52:44,600 --> 00:52:46,480
Help Jerry's kids?
救救谢利的孩子？

578
00:52:46,800 --> 00:52:49,120
- Scientology?
- For nuclear power?
-科学教派？
-为核能？

579
00:52:54,160 --> 00:52:55,800
(自助行李提取)

580
00:52:56,080 --> 00:53:00,240
<i>Your attention, please.
No-frills passengers now arriving.</i>
各位注意，乘客正在抵达

581
00:53:00,560 --> 00:53:03,840
<i>Please have your baggage
claim checks ready to show</i>
请在离开机场前

582
00:53:04,040 --> 00:53:06,080
<i>upon leaving the terminal.</i>
提取及检查行李

583
00:53:06,360 --> 00:53:09,080
This guy has no airline experience.
他没有驾驶航机经验

584
00:53:09,360 --> 00:53:13,480
He's a menace to everything in the air.
Yes, birds, too.
他在空中对一切构成危险
包括雀鸟在内

585
00:53:13,680 --> 00:53:16,880
OK, he's a terrible risk,
but what other choice have we got?
他是一大危机
但我们别无他选

586
00:53:17,160 --> 00:53:20,200
That's the whole story, Rex.
Everything we know.
我们所知的就这么多

587
00:53:21,280 --> 00:53:26,000
Let's face a few facts.
I flew with Striker during the war.
告诉你，我曾在战时与史合作

588
00:53:26,320 --> 00:53:30,000
He can't afford to worry about those
times when... things weren't so good.
当事情不顺利，他就方英寸大乱

589
00:53:30,280 --> 00:53:33,720
- Right now things aren't so good.
- Let me tell you something.
-现在事情亦不顺利
-让我告诉你

590
00:53:34,000 --> 00:53:37,320
Striker was a top-notch
squadron leader long ago.
史泰德很久之前
是空军部队队长

591
00:53:37,520 --> 00:53:41,160
Get on the horn
and talk that guy down.
去说服他吧！

592
00:53:41,400 --> 00:53:44,360
Let him get the feel
of that airplane,
让他有信心驾驶飞机

593
00:53:44,640 --> 00:53:48,320
then you'll have to talk him
right down to the ground.
然后令他安全着陆吧！

594
00:53:50,680 --> 00:53:54,640
- Very well. Put Striker on the speaker.
- Use my radio.
-好，联络史泰德吧！
-用我的无线电

595
00:53:56,600 --> 00:53:59,040
I picked the wrong week
to quit drinking.
我不该选这星期戒酒

596
00:54:01,560 --> 00:54:04,440
You can work them direct
from here, Captain.
上尉，你由此直接跟他们说吧

597
00:54:06,480 --> 00:54:11,320
Striker? Striker, this is
Captain Rex Kramer speaking.
史泰德，我是祈力斯上尉

598
00:54:14,680 --> 00:54:18,040
Yes, Captain Kramer.
Read you loud and clear.
我听到，祈上尉

599
00:54:21,360 --> 00:54:24,320
All right.
It's obvious you remember me.
很好，你仍记得我

600
00:54:24,600 --> 00:54:27,960
What do you say we forget about
everything, except what we must do?
不如我们忘记一切，放眼现在

601
00:54:28,920 --> 00:54:30,800
Let's not kid each other, Kramer.
少来这套了

602
00:54:31,040 --> 00:54:35,040
You know I've never flown a bucket
like this. I'll need all the luck there is.
你也知我从没驾驶过这种飞机
一切唯有靠运气

603
00:54:35,320 --> 00:54:37,520
Stand by, Striker.
准备好，史泰德

604
00:54:37,800 --> 00:54:42,360
Our one hope is to build this man up.
I've got to give him confidence.
我们要令他有自信
觉得自己可以胜任

605
00:54:42,600 --> 00:54:46,840
<i>- You ever flown a multi-engine plane?
- No, never.</i>
-驾驶过多引擎飞机吗？
-从来没有

606
00:54:47,120 --> 00:54:49,440
Shit! It's a goddamn waste of time.
岂有此理！这简直浪费时间

607
00:54:49,680 --> 00:54:53,720
<i>- There's no way he can land it!
- You got to talk him down!</i>
-他没可能令飞机降落
-你得说服他！

608
00:54:54,040 --> 00:54:56,960
<i>Route him into Lake Michigan.
At least avoid killing innocent people.</i>
叫他飞往密芝根
这样不会连累无辜

609
00:54:57,240 --> 00:54:59,640
You're the only chance they've got.
你是他们唯一的希望

610
00:55:02,360 --> 00:55:04,440
All right.
好吧

611
00:55:04,720 --> 00:55:07,560
Striker, you listen,
and you listen close.
史，你好好听着

612
00:55:08,640 --> 00:55:10,440
Flying a plane
is like riding a bicycle.
驾驶飞机就像骑单车一样

613
00:55:11,200 --> 00:55:15,960
<i>It'sjust harder to put baseball cards
in the spokes. Get the feel of the plane.</i>
只不过是较复杂一些
你得掌握个中窍门

614
00:55:16,240 --> 00:55:18,920
Later, we'll run down
the landing procedure.
稍后我们会教你着陆程序

615
00:55:23,520 --> 00:55:26,360
All right.
Disengage the automatic pilot.
好，先拆去自动机师

616
00:55:26,640 --> 00:55:30,000
Make no violent control movements
like you did in the fighter planes.
就像你驾驶战机时般
别令飞机强烈摆动

617
00:55:30,920 --> 00:55:33,800
All right.
I'll unlock the automatic pilot.
好，我会放走自动机师

618
00:55:39,360 --> 00:55:42,680
<i>The controls will feel very heavy
compared to a fighter.</i>
操纵杆会比战机的重

619
00:55:44,640 --> 00:55:47,840
<i>Don't worry about that.
It's perfectly normal.</i>
别担心，这是正常的

620
00:55:59,400 --> 00:56:00,720
<i>Now, one more thing.</i>
有一件事

621
00:56:00,960 --> 00:56:04,440
<i>Can somebody work the radio
and leave you free for flying?</i>
可否找人来负责无线电通讯？

622
00:56:04,680 --> 00:56:09,320
<i>- The stewardess is here with me.
- Have her sit in the co-pilot seat.</i>
-空姐就在我旁
-她可以坐到副机师位置

623
00:56:11,360 --> 00:56:14,400
Elaine, he wants you
to sit in the co-pilot seat.
绮莲，他想你坐到副机师座位

624
00:56:22,240 --> 00:56:24,600
What's going on?
We have a right to know the truth.
发生什么事？我们有权知道

625
00:56:26,320 --> 00:56:28,200
All right, I'll level with you all.
好，我会向你们坦白

626
00:56:28,480 --> 00:56:31,320
The most important thing
is that you remain calm.
最重要是保持冷静

627
00:56:31,640 --> 00:56:33,560
There's no reason to panic.
绝对不用惊慌

628
00:56:33,800 --> 00:56:36,800
It's true one of the crew members is ill.
我们确有一名机员病倒

629
00:56:37,080 --> 00:56:38,760
Slightly ill.
有些少不舒服

630
00:56:39,040 --> 00:56:41,320
The other two pilots are fine.
但另外两名机师没事

631
00:56:41,600 --> 00:56:45,840
They're flying the plane, free to pursue
a life of religious fulfilment.
他们正在驾驶飞机，全力以赴

632
00:56:46,600 --> 00:56:50,880
The radio is all yours. Keep an eye
on number three engine gauge.
你来负责无线电通讯
留意第三号引擎表板

633
00:56:51,120 --> 00:56:52,480
It's running a little hot.
有点热

634
00:56:52,800 --> 00:56:55,520
(有点热)

635
00:56:55,800 --> 00:56:58,640
<i>Striker, first I'd like to say something.</i>
史，首先我要说…

636
00:56:59,280 --> 00:57:02,320
I know things must look
pretty rough up there.
我知道现在你那处一定一团糟

637
00:57:02,560 --> 00:57:05,080
If you do what I tell you
when I tell you,
但若你一切都依我的

638
00:57:05,320 --> 00:57:07,760
<i>there's no reason
you should lack confidence</i>
你不该没有自信

639
00:57:08,040 --> 00:57:11,360
<i>in your chances of coming out
alive and in one piece.</i>
你绝对做得到的

640
00:57:11,640 --> 00:57:13,800
What weather are you in?
天气如何？

641
00:57:14,960 --> 00:57:17,120
- Rain.
- And a little ice.
-有雨
-还有些冰雹

642
00:57:17,400 --> 00:57:18,840
And a little ice.
还有些冰雹

643
00:57:19,120 --> 00:57:24,840
- How's it handling?
- Sluggish. Like a wet sponge.
-情况怎样？
-不大好，湿透了

644
00:57:25,120 --> 00:57:27,400
Sluggish. Like a wet sponge.
不大好，湿透了

645
00:57:27,640 --> 00:57:30,320
All right, Striker.
You're doing just fine.
史泰德，你做得很好

646
00:57:31,440 --> 00:57:34,560
It's damn good
he doesn't know I hate his guts.
幸好他不知道我很讨厌他

647
00:57:34,800 --> 00:57:38,160
It's damn good
you don't know he hates your guts.
幸好你不知道我很讨厌你

648
00:57:44,600 --> 00:57:47,120
Can I get you something?
有什么可以帮忙？

649
00:57:52,600 --> 00:57:55,360
I'm sorry. I don't understand.
抱歉，我不明白

650
00:57:55,640 --> 00:57:58,720
- Stewardess. I speak jive.
- Good.
-小姐，我懂说非洲话
-好极了

651
00:57:59,040 --> 00:58:03,400
He said he's in great pain, and he
wants to know if you can help him?
他说很痛苦，想你帮助他

652
00:58:03,680 --> 00:58:07,720
Tell him to relax.
I'll be back with some medicine.
叫他放松，我拿药来

653
00:58:10,720 --> 00:58:14,920
Just hang loose, blood.
She'll get some medicine.
放松，她会拿药来

654
00:58:15,160 --> 00:58:17,560
My Mama didn't raise no dummies,
that's obvious.
我并非省油的灯

655
00:58:17,800 --> 00:58:20,440
Cut me some slack, Jack.
别说废话了

656
00:58:23,280 --> 00:58:26,800
Chump don't want no help,
chump don't get the help.
他不想帮忙…

657
00:58:27,080 --> 00:58:30,040
That dude's got no brains, anyhow.
那厮是没有脑袋的

658
00:58:36,360 --> 00:58:39,320
Let Captain Oveur's wife
know what's going on.
通知欧机长的太太吧！

659
00:58:39,560 --> 00:58:41,960
This weather bulletin
just came off the wire.
刚收到最新的天气报告

660
00:58:44,440 --> 00:58:47,160
- What can you make out of this?
- This?
-你认为怎样？
-这个？

661
00:58:47,440 --> 00:58:51,200
I can make a hat or a brooch
or pterodactyl...
我可以用来做帽子
胸针或无尾飞机…

662
00:59:00,480 --> 00:59:02,560
- Hello?
- Mrs Oveur?
-你好
-欧太太？

663
00:59:02,800 --> 00:59:04,520
Yes, this is Mrs Oveur.
对，我是

664
00:59:04,760 --> 00:59:09,200
<i>This is Ed Macias at the airport.
There's trouble on your husband's flight.</i>
我是机场的马艾迪
你丈夫的航机遇上麻烦

665
00:59:09,480 --> 00:59:11,400
<i>We don't know how serious it is,</i>
我们并不知道情况有多严重

666
00:59:11,720 --> 00:59:14,440
<i>but Steve McCroskey thought
you'd want to come over.</i>
但麦斯堤认为你最好来这里

667
00:59:14,720 --> 00:59:16,920
Yes. I'll be right down.
好，我立即来

668
00:59:20,400 --> 00:59:24,360
I've got to go to the airport. You can
let yourself out the back door.
我得往机场，你由后门走吧

669
00:59:24,600 --> 00:59:26,800
There's juice in the refrigerator.
冰箱里有果汁

670
00:59:35,000 --> 00:59:39,560
Doctor says the sick people are getting
worse. We're running out of time.
医生说病人情况转坏
我们时间无多了

671
00:59:41,400 --> 00:59:44,080
<i>I've got to concentrate.</i>
我得集中精神

672
00:59:45,160 --> 00:59:47,840
<i>I've got to concentrate.</i>
我得集中精神

673
00:59:49,280 --> 00:59:51,240
<i>Hello?</i>
有人吗？

674
00:59:52,400 --> 00:59:54,600
<i>Echo!</i>
回音！

675
00:59:55,400 --> 00:59:58,760
<i>Pinch hitting for Pedro Bourbone,</i>
拳打柏度

676
00:59:58,960 --> 01:00:00,960
<i>Manny Mota.</i>
脚踢文尼

677
01:00:04,600 --> 01:00:08,000
- How you doing, honey?
- Jack, I'm so hot, I'm burning up.
-老婆，怎么了？
-我很热，像被火烧

678
01:00:08,240 --> 01:00:10,160
I'll turn on some air.
我开窗吧

679
01:00:15,720 --> 01:00:19,120
- What's going on?
- Close the window!
-发生什么事？
-关窗！

680
01:00:20,120 --> 01:00:23,760
Chicago, the passengers
are panicking. When do we start down?
乘客开始恐慌
何时可以降落？

681
01:00:24,080 --> 01:00:28,040
Not yet. You'll be in radar range
any second now.
还未可以
你该快进入雷达范围了

682
01:00:28,320 --> 01:00:30,920
They should have been in range
10 minutes ago.
他们该在十分钟前已进入范围

683
01:00:31,800 --> 01:00:35,360
Gunderson, check the radar range.
Anything yet?
古达臣，再查看雷达
有何发现？

684
01:00:35,640 --> 01:00:37,720
About two more minutes, chief.
尚要两分钟

685
01:00:41,480 --> 01:00:45,360
- They could be miles off course.
- Impossible! They're on instruments.
-他们可能偏离了航道
-没可能！是自动导航！

686
01:00:49,160 --> 01:00:51,480
This is going to be a real sweat.
今次一定很惊险

687
01:00:52,320 --> 01:00:54,560
Gunderson,
let me know when you get anything.
古达臣，有最新消息就通知我

688
01:00:54,840 --> 01:00:57,840
- Got a cigarette, Nels?
- I can't take much more of this.
-尼斯，有香烟吗？
-我再也受不了

689
01:01:01,960 --> 01:01:05,040
Looks like I picked the wrong week
to quit amphetamines.
似乎我选错这星期戒安非他命

690
01:01:06,080 --> 01:01:07,760
- How about some more coffee?
- No, thanks.
-喝点咖啡吗？
-不用，谢谢

691
01:01:08,000 --> 01:01:10,280
These reporters want a statement.
这些记者想你发表声明

692
01:01:10,520 --> 01:01:13,960
- How much longer can they hold out?
- 30, 45 minutes.
-他们能支持多久？
-三十到四十五分钟

693
01:01:14,200 --> 01:01:16,480
- Who's flying the plane?
- A passenger.
-由谁来驾驶飞机？
-一名乘客

694
01:01:16,760 --> 01:01:21,000
He's an experienced air-force pilot.
No cause for alarm. Take over.
他是一名富经验的空军机师
不用担心，你来吧

695
01:01:21,240 --> 01:01:24,520
- What kind of plane?
- It's a big, pretty white plane
-是怎样的飞机？
-又大又漂亮的白色飞机

696
01:01:24,760 --> 01:01:29,800
with red stripes, curtains
and wheels. It looks like a big Tylenol.
有红色条子、窗帘、轮子
就像一架大模型

697
01:01:30,720 --> 01:01:33,000
OK, boys. Let's get some pictures.
好，拿些照片吧！

698
01:01:43,960 --> 01:01:46,360
(航机乘客大难临头)

699
01:01:48,640 --> 01:01:51,080
(芝加哥机长作出最坏打算)

700
01:01:53,600 --> 01:01:56,680
(男孩被困在冰箱
吃掉自己的脚)

701
01:01:59,160 --> 01:02:01,160
(危机)

702
01:02:01,440 --> 01:02:04,520
<i>This bulletinjust handed to me.
Stricken airliner approaching Chicago.</i>
最新消息，那航机飞往芝加哥

703
01:02:18,440 --> 01:02:21,200
Shana, they bought their tickets.
他们自作自受

704
01:02:21,480 --> 01:02:24,000
They knew what
they were getting into.
他们早知道有危险

705
01:02:25,320 --> 01:02:28,160
I say, let them crash!
让航机坠毁吧

706
01:02:42,880 --> 01:02:45,840
- Would you like some whisky, ma'am?
- Certainly not!
-要威士忌吗？
-不要

707
01:02:57,600 --> 01:02:59,640
How are the passengers?
乘客怎么样？

708
01:02:59,920 --> 01:03:03,560
I won't deceive you, Mr Striker.
We're running out of time.
我不会骗你，我们时间无多了

709
01:03:03,840 --> 01:03:07,640
- Surely, there's something you can do.
- I'm doing everything I can...
-你一定可以做什么的
-我已尽一切办法…

710
01:03:07,880 --> 01:03:09,880
and stop calling me Shirley.
也不要再说我有办法

711
01:03:33,080 --> 01:03:35,480
Randy, are you all right?
兰迪，你没事吧？

712
01:03:35,720 --> 01:03:37,720
Oh, Dr Rumack.
雷医生

713
01:03:39,200 --> 01:03:42,240
I'm scared. I've never been so scared...
我很害怕，从没这般害怕

714
01:03:43,400 --> 01:03:46,480
And besides,
I'm 26 and I'm not married.
而且我26岁了，还未结婚

715
01:03:46,760 --> 01:03:50,040
We're going to make it.
You've got to believe that.
我们定会成功的，你定要相信

716
01:03:50,280 --> 01:03:53,200
Dr Rumack, do you have any idea
when we'll be landing?
雷医生，知否我们何时着陆？

717
01:03:53,480 --> 01:03:56,000
Pretty soon. How are you bearing up?
快了，你觉得怎样？

718
01:03:56,280 --> 01:03:59,000
To be honest,
I've never been so scared,
坦白说，我从来没那么惊慌过

719
01:03:59,240 --> 01:04:01,560
but at least I have a husband.
但幸好我有丈夫

720
01:04:13,960 --> 01:04:17,160
<i>Stay in formation.
Target'sjust ahead.</i>
保持队形，目标就在前面

721
01:04:17,320 --> 01:04:20,200
<i>Target should be clear
if you go in low enough.</i>
若飞得够低，该能看清楚目标

722
01:04:20,480 --> 01:04:23,840
<i>You'll have to decide.
You'll have to decide.</i>
你得决定…

723
01:04:24,080 --> 01:04:26,080
<i>You'll have to decide.</i>
你得决定

724
01:04:26,400 --> 01:04:29,600
<i>Stay in formation.
Target'sjust ahead.</i>
保持队形，目标就在前面

725
01:04:29,800 --> 01:04:32,680
<i>Target should be clear
if you go in low enough.</i>
若飞得够低，该看清楚目标

726
01:04:32,960 --> 01:04:36,160
<i>You'll have to decide.
You'll have to decide.</i>
你得决定…

727
01:04:36,400 --> 01:04:37,720
<i>You'll have to decide.</i>
你得决定

728
01:04:42,880 --> 01:04:46,000
Oh, rats! Lost number four.
糟糕！四号引擎没有了

729
01:04:46,280 --> 01:04:48,440
What happened? What went wrong?
发生什么事？有何不妥？

730
01:04:48,680 --> 01:04:51,400
I forgot to check the oil pressure.
我忘了检查油压

731
01:04:52,240 --> 01:04:55,320
When Kramer hears about this,
the shit's going to hit the fan.
若给祈力斯知道，定给他臭骂

732
01:04:57,920 --> 01:05:00,400
I told him to watch that
oil temperature. What's he doing?
早叫他检查油压，他怎么了？

733
01:05:00,640 --> 01:05:03,440
Stiker, that plane can't land itself.
史泰德，飞机无法自行降落

734
01:05:03,720 --> 01:05:07,120
Ease off. It's not his fault.
It could happen to any pilot.
这不是他的错
任何机师都可能会这样

735
01:05:07,400 --> 01:05:08,560
It happened to Barbara Stanwyck.
施丹域亦出现这情形

736
01:05:08,800 --> 01:05:12,000
Can't push him too hard. Might break.
Remember who you're dealing with.
别逼得他太紧，他可能会崩溃

737
01:05:12,280 --> 01:05:15,080
Nick, Pete, Jerry,
there's a fire in the barn.
尼克、彼得、谢利，紧急状态

738
01:05:16,720 --> 01:05:19,400
He's right.
I can't take the pressure.
他说得对，我应付不了压力

739
01:05:20,400 --> 01:05:22,120
I was crazy to think
I could land this plane.
我以为可以令飞机降落
实在妄想

740
01:05:22,400 --> 01:05:28,000
- But, Ted, you're the only...
- I don't care. I don't have what it takes.
-泰德，只有你…
-我不管，我没有这个能力

741
01:05:28,240 --> 01:05:31,720
They'd be better off with someone
who's never flown before.
找过从没驾驶过飞机的人来
结果可能更好

742
01:05:41,320 --> 01:05:43,480
Bad news. Fog's getting thicker.
坏消息，雾越来越浓

743
01:05:44,680 --> 01:05:47,680
And Leon's getting larger.
李安亦越来越大

744
01:06:10,760 --> 01:06:14,040
I know what you're going to say,
so save your breath.
我知道你想说什么，省口气吧

745
01:06:15,920 --> 01:06:18,640
Well, I don't have a thing to say.
我并没想要说什么

746
01:06:19,440 --> 01:06:21,520
You've done the best you could.
你已尽了力

747
01:06:21,760 --> 01:06:24,120
You really have. The best you could.
真的，你已尽了力

748
01:06:25,240 --> 01:06:27,600
We can't expect to win them all.
凡事岂能尽如人意

749
01:06:29,120 --> 01:06:33,720
I want to tell you something I've
kept to myself through these years.
告诉你我保守了多年的秘密

750
01:06:34,000 --> 01:06:36,720
I was in the war. Medical corps.
我在战时是军医

751
01:06:37,680 --> 01:06:42,560
One night, they brought in
a badly wounded pilot from a raid.
有一晚他们送来一名重伤机师

752
01:06:42,800 --> 01:06:44,840
He could barely talk.
他几乎不能说话

753
01:06:45,080 --> 01:06:48,040
He looked up at me, he said,
但他望着我说

754
01:06:48,280 --> 01:06:52,160
"The odds were against us up there,
but we went in anyway.
“我们形势不利
但还是勇往直前”

755
01:06:52,440 --> 01:06:56,080
"I'm glad.
Captain made the right decision."
“我很高兴
上尉作出正确决定”

756
01:06:58,040 --> 01:07:00,920
The pilot's name was George Zip.
那机师的名字叫做薛佐治

757
01:07:02,320 --> 01:07:04,600
George Zip said that?
薛佐治说的？

758
01:07:05,800 --> 01:07:10,080
The last thing he said to me,
"Doc," he said, "Sometime...
他最后对我说： “医生…”

759
01:07:11,480 --> 01:07:13,640
"...the crew is up against it.
“队员都全力以赴”

760
01:07:13,880 --> 01:07:15,840
"The breaks are beating the boys.
“我们虽然受到挫折”

761
01:07:16,120 --> 01:07:19,120
"Tell them to give it all they've got
“但告诉他们要倾尽全力”

762
01:07:20,600 --> 01:07:23,640
"and win just one for the Zipper.
“为部队胜出一仗”

763
01:07:25,760 --> 01:07:28,040
"I don't know
where I'll be then," he said...
“到时我不知道
自己会身在何处”

764
01:07:30,040 --> 01:07:33,120
"but I won't smell too good,
that's for sure."
“但肯定已全身发臭”

765
01:07:35,520 --> 01:07:37,320
Excuse me, Doc.
医生，失陪

766
01:07:38,200 --> 01:07:40,280
I've got a plane to land.
我要令飞机着陆

767
01:07:47,880 --> 01:07:51,760
<i>You'd better stay up there a bit.
When the fog lifts, we'll bring you in.</i>
留在上空，待大雾消散才降落

768
01:07:52,000 --> 01:07:53,920
I'll take it, Elaine.
绮莲，让我来

769
01:08:01,560 --> 01:08:05,560
Listen, Dr Rumack says the sick
people are in critical condition.
听着，雷医生说病人情况危殆

770
01:08:05,880 --> 01:08:08,600
Every minute counts.
We've got to land now.
每分每秒都很重要
要现在降落了

771
01:08:08,920 --> 01:08:12,760
Don't be a fool, Striker. You know
what a landing like this means.
别傻了
你也知道这样降落结果会如何

772
01:08:13,040 --> 01:08:14,680
I'm ordering you to stay up there!
我命令你继续在上空

773
01:08:14,960 --> 01:08:16,640
No dice, Chicago.
不行

774
01:08:16,920 --> 01:08:19,480
I'm giving the orders,
and we're coming in.
现在由我话事，我们要降落了

775
01:08:19,760 --> 01:08:22,440
I guess the foot's
on the other hand now.
现在他反客为主了

776
01:08:25,280 --> 01:08:27,200
He'll never make it in this soup.
这样大雾，他是不会成功的

777
01:08:27,480 --> 01:08:30,800
But it's his ship now. He's in charge.
但现在由他话事了

778
01:08:31,080 --> 01:08:33,840
He's the boss, head man, top dog,
他是老板、上头、首领…

779
01:08:34,080 --> 01:08:37,120
- big cheese, head honcho...
- Captain, look at this!
-领袖、老大…
-上尉，看！

780
01:08:38,720 --> 01:08:40,800
"Passengers certain to die."
“乘客必死无疑”

781
01:08:41,040 --> 01:08:43,040
"Airline negligent."
“航空当局疏忽”

782
01:08:43,360 --> 01:08:45,240
There's a sale at Penny's!
百货公司大减价！

783
01:08:48,200 --> 01:08:51,160
I'll need three men up in the tower.
You, Neubauer, you, Macias.
我要三人往控制塔
黎保家、马卡斯

784
01:08:51,440 --> 01:08:53,280
Me John. Big tree.
还有我， “大树”约翰

785
01:08:54,360 --> 01:08:57,000
Striker, we're going to the tower.
Good luck.
史，我们准备往控制塔
祝你好运

786
01:08:57,760 --> 01:09:00,920
- We're going to the tower.
- The tower! The tower!
-我们准备往控制塔
-控制塔

787
01:09:01,120 --> 01:09:03,360
Rapunzel! Rapunzel!
林宝素…

788
01:09:07,680 --> 01:09:10,160
Stewardess, how soon till we land?
小姐，尚有多久才降落？

789
01:09:10,440 --> 01:09:13,080
It won't be long now.
Try not to worry.
快了，别担心

790
01:09:26,240 --> 01:09:29,760
We're all ready, sir. Captain
McCroskey, this is Captain Roberts.
我们准备好了
麦机长，这是罗机长

791
01:09:30,040 --> 01:09:33,680
Captain Kramer, Captain Colosimo.
Captain Hinshaw, Captain Gantz.
祈上尉、高机长
韩机长、简机长

792
01:09:33,920 --> 01:09:37,520
Captain Kramer, Captain Gantz.
Captain Hinshaw, Captain Roberts.
祈上尉、简机长
韩机长、罗机长

793
01:09:37,760 --> 01:09:39,520
Colosimo, you work the relay.
高，你负责联络

794
01:09:39,840 --> 01:09:41,720
Roberts, check air traffic.
罗，看看航空交通

795
01:09:42,480 --> 01:09:45,040
Get that finger out of your ear.
You don't know where it's been.
拿出手指来，很脏的

796
01:09:48,000 --> 01:09:49,920
- Steve!
- Got a cigarette, Nels?
-史堤
-尼斯，有香烟吗？

797
01:09:50,160 --> 01:09:53,840
Linda, your husband and the others
are alive but unconscious.
莲黛，你的丈夫
和其他人仍活着，但昏迷了

798
01:09:54,120 --> 01:09:56,000
Just like Gerald Ford.
就像福特

799
01:09:56,240 --> 01:10:00,160
There's a chance we can save them
if Striker lands that plane in time.
若史及时降落
我们便有机会救他们

800
01:10:00,440 --> 01:10:03,040
- That isn't much of a chance, is it?
- I don't know.
-但机会不大吧？
-不知道

801
01:10:03,320 --> 01:10:05,880
We're doing everything we can.
Now excuse me.
我们已尽了力，失陪

802
01:10:09,560 --> 01:10:12,120
Where did you get that dress?
It's awful!
你从哪儿买来这裙子？很难看

803
01:10:12,360 --> 01:10:15,200
And those shoes and that coat! Geez!
还有这对鞋和大衣，天啊！

804
01:10:19,280 --> 01:10:22,760
8 miles. Turn right to heading 044.
八哩，转右往044

805
01:10:25,000 --> 01:10:27,880
<i>We're now at 2,000 feet
beginning our descent.</i>
我们现在于二千英尺上空
开始降落

806
01:10:28,160 --> 01:10:32,440
- Pour every light onto that field.
- It's being done.
-把跑道所有灯亮起
-已经这样做了

807
01:10:36,720 --> 01:10:39,840
Tower to all emergency vehicles,
runway is niner.
控制塔呼叫所有救急汽车
前往九号跑道

808
01:10:40,840 --> 01:10:43,360
<i>Airport vehicles,
take positions one and two.</i>
机场汽车，一、二号准备

809
01:10:43,600 --> 01:10:45,600
Civilian equipment, number three.
平民器材，三号

810
01:10:47,760 --> 01:10:50,160
<i>Air force, positions four and five.</i>
空军，四、五号

811
01:10:50,440 --> 01:10:52,640
<i>All ambulances go to number three.</i>
所有救护车往三号站

812
01:10:52,880 --> 01:10:55,760
<i>Air Israel, please clear the runway.</i>
以色列航机，请驶离跑道

813
01:11:01,440 --> 01:11:04,320
In a moment, we'll ask you
to assume crash positions.
我们将要你们摆出撞击姿势

814
01:11:04,600 --> 01:11:07,240
Life jackets are under your seat.
椅子下面有救生衣

815
01:11:07,520 --> 01:11:12,400
Place it over your head. When I give the
word, pull the cord on the right side flap.
套上去，我一声令下
就拉右面的绳子

816
01:11:14,360 --> 01:11:17,520
Your seat cushions are also equipped
with a flotation device.
你们的椅垫都有浮水设计

817
01:11:18,640 --> 01:11:22,720
<i>WZAZ in Chicago,
where disco lives forever.</i>
芝加哥的WAZA电台
永远为你播放

818
01:11:26,320 --> 01:11:28,680
Your altitude's too erratic.
你的飞行高度忽高忽低

819
01:11:28,920 --> 01:11:32,200
You can't come straight in.
You've got enough fuel for two hours.
不能降落
你尚有两小时的燃料

820
01:11:33,200 --> 01:11:36,360
I'll take it, Elaine.
Listen to me, Kramer.
绮莲，让我来…祈，你听着

821
01:11:36,600 --> 01:11:40,240
We have people up here who will die
in less than an hour.
机上有人在不足一小时后
就会死去

822
01:11:40,520 --> 01:11:42,720
I may bend your airplane,
but I'll get it down.
我或会令飞机损毁
但我可以成功降落的

823
01:11:42,920 --> 01:11:45,120
I'm putting the landing gear down.
我要放下降落架了

824
01:11:45,360 --> 01:11:49,080
- The passengers are ready.
- Thanks, Randy.
-乘客都准备好了
-劳驾

825
01:11:49,400 --> 01:11:52,280
You better leave, sweetheart.
You might get hurt up here.
你还是出去吧！
在这儿你可能会受伤

826
01:12:01,920 --> 01:12:04,960
- Ted...
- Yes?
-泰德
-什么事？

827
01:12:05,960 --> 01:12:09,160
I wanted you to know... now...
我想你知道…现在…

828
01:12:09,440 --> 01:12:11,360
I'm very proud.
我以你为傲

829
01:12:15,200 --> 01:12:17,640
Tell them the gear is down
and we're ready to land.
告诉他们降落架已放下
我们准备降落

830
01:12:21,360 --> 01:12:24,200
The gear is down,
and we're ready to land.
降落架已放下，我们准备降落

831
01:12:26,040 --> 01:12:29,640
All right. He's on final now. Put out
all runway lights except niner.
好，已进入最后阶段
只亮起九号跑道的灯

832
01:12:31,720 --> 01:12:35,400
Captain, maybe we ought
to turn on the searchlights now.
上尉，我们或许该亮起搜索灯

833
01:12:36,200 --> 01:12:37,880
No.
不

834
01:12:38,160 --> 01:12:41,640
That's just what they'll
be expecting us to do.
他们就是以为我们会这样做

835
01:12:46,160 --> 01:12:49,680
I want to tell you both good luck.
We're all counting on you.
祝你们好运，我们全看你们了

836
01:12:51,760 --> 01:12:56,080
Now listen carefully. You'll see
the runway at 300 feet.
小心听着，在三百英尺高度
你便会见到跑道

837
01:12:56,320 --> 01:13:01,200
Aim to touch down a third of the way.
A slight cross wind, so be ready.
在跑道三分一位置时着陆
有微风，准备好

838
01:13:02,240 --> 01:13:06,520
If you land too fast, use your emergency
brakes. Red handle's right in front.
若着陆得太快，用紧急煞掣
即右前方的红色手掣

839
01:13:06,800 --> 01:13:08,880
If that doesn't stop you...
若这样还不停下

840
01:13:13,880 --> 01:13:17,440
If that doesn't stop you,
cut the four ignition switches.
就熄掉四个引擎

841
01:13:21,080 --> 01:13:25,080
Can you see us now? You should
be able to see the field.
看到我们没有？
你该看到机场了

842
01:13:32,000 --> 01:13:35,160
- Sure is quiet out there.
- Yeah, too quiet.
-外面很平静
-对，太平静了

843
01:13:37,120 --> 01:13:40,240
Looks like I picked the wrong week
to quit sniffing glue.
似乎我选错了这星期戒闻胶水

844
01:13:52,760 --> 01:13:54,560
There it is.
它来了！

845
01:13:56,680 --> 01:13:58,200
There he is!
他来了！

846
01:13:59,800 --> 01:14:03,280
- You're coming in too fast.
- I know, I know!
-速度太快了
-我知道…

847
01:14:03,560 --> 01:14:05,240
He knows, he knows!
他知道…

848
01:14:08,000 --> 01:14:10,280
Below 700 now. Still going down.
现在低于七百英尺，仍在下降

849
01:14:10,520 --> 01:14:15,800
675, 650, 625, he's holding.
No, he's down, he's down.
675英尺、650英尺、625英尺
稳住了，不，正下降

850
01:14:16,120 --> 01:14:17,960
Sound your alarm now.
发出警号吧

851
01:14:19,920 --> 01:14:22,440
Now, everybody,
get in crash positions.
大家请准备撞机

852
01:14:27,640 --> 01:14:29,400
Put down 30 degrees of flap.
风门翼要三十度

853
01:14:33,160 --> 01:14:37,920
Listen to me. Remember your brakes
and switches. Get ready to flare it out!
听着，煞掣，按钮，准备

854
01:14:38,680 --> 01:14:43,640
He's all over the place.
900 up to 1,300 feet. What an asshole.
他一时在九百英尺
一时在一千三百英尺，真是笨蛋

855
01:14:43,920 --> 01:14:46,440
<i>More left rudder. Put down more flap.</i>
靠左，风门翼更加偏侧

856
01:14:51,760 --> 01:14:53,480
Just kidding!
开玩笑而已

857
01:14:54,600 --> 01:14:57,400
<i>Striker, lift your nose.
Straighten your wings.</i>
史，升起机头，伸直机翼

858
01:14:57,680 --> 01:15:00,440
Coming in too fast. Watch your speed.
太快了，留意速度

859
01:15:00,680 --> 01:15:02,680
He's coming right at us!
他向我们冲来！

860
01:15:06,760 --> 01:15:09,840
Coming in too hot.
Ease up on the throttle.
太快了，减慢速度

861
01:15:10,120 --> 01:15:14,600
<i>Watch out for that cross wind.
Level it out. Dip your left wing.</i>
留意风向，左翼倾侧

862
01:15:18,240 --> 01:15:21,520
<i>You're drifting. Keep your eyes
on the far end of the runway.</i>
你偏离了航道，望着跑道末端

863
01:15:24,080 --> 01:15:25,520
<i>You're too low, damn it!</i>
太低了，糟糕！

864
01:15:27,240 --> 01:15:28,880
<i>Watch your stall speed.</i>
留意速度

865
01:15:32,120 --> 01:15:33,560
<i>Flare it out!</i>
慢慢降落！

866
01:15:36,240 --> 01:15:38,040
Ease her down. Down!
慢慢让它着陆，着陆吧！

867
01:15:42,400 --> 01:15:44,920
<i>The brake! Pull the red handle!</i>
煞掣！拉那红色手掣！

868
01:15:49,880 --> 01:15:53,600
I want to tell you both good luck.
We're all counting on you.
祝你俩好运，我们全看你们了

869
01:15:59,360 --> 01:16:02,920
<i>Flight 209 now arriving at gate eight.</i>
209号班机正抵达八号闸

870
01:16:04,000 --> 01:16:05,760
<i>Gate nine.</i>
九号闸

871
01:16:06,040 --> 01:16:07,360
<i>Gate ten.</i>
十号闸

872
01:16:07,960 --> 01:16:10,040
<i>Pull out of it! Push that button!</i>
拉！按钮！

873
01:16:16,600 --> 01:16:19,800
<i>Gate 13... Gate 14.</i>
十三号闸，十四号闸

874
01:16:20,040 --> 01:16:21,280
<i>Gate 15...</i>
十五号闸

875
01:16:30,600 --> 01:16:33,760
Auntie Em! Toto! It's a twister!
天啊！它在旋转！

876
01:16:36,240 --> 01:16:39,680
<i>Gate 23, 24, 25...</i>
23号闸，24号闸，25号闸…

877
01:17:01,960 --> 01:17:05,480
I want to tell you both good luck.
We're all counting on you.
祝你俩好运，我们全看你们了

878
01:17:11,080 --> 01:17:12,320
<i>Striker?</i>
史泰德？

879
01:17:12,600 --> 01:17:16,560
<i>- Striker, are you all right?
- Yeah. We're OK.</i>
-史泰德，你没事吧？
-我们没事

880
01:17:17,200 --> 01:17:21,480
That was probably the lousiest landing
in the history of this airport.
这大概是本机场最拙劣的降落

881
01:17:22,440 --> 01:17:24,280
But some of us, particularly me,
但我们有好些人，特别是我

882
01:17:24,520 --> 01:17:28,480
<i>would like to buy you a drink
and shake your hand.</i>
想请你喝东西和与你握手

883
01:17:33,280 --> 01:17:36,040
<i>And, Ted, when the going got rough...</i>
泰德，当遇上困难…

884
01:17:38,840 --> 01:17:41,280
Have a nice day. OK.
祝你愉快

885
01:17:41,520 --> 01:17:44,480
Have a nice day and thank you
for flying TransAmerican.
祝你愉快，多谢乘搭本班航机

886
01:17:45,240 --> 01:17:49,960
<i>Loneliness, that's the bottom line.
I was never happy as a child.</i>
寂寞是底线，儿时我从不快乐

887
01:17:50,240 --> 01:17:53,480
<i>Christmas, what does that mean
to you? Mine was a living hell.</i>
圣诞对你有何意义？
对我来说则是活受罪

888
01:17:54,480 --> 01:17:57,960
Do you know what it's like to fall
in the mud and get kicked in the head
你知否掉在泥泞上
被铁靴踢头…

889
01:17:58,240 --> 01:18:00,320
by an iron boot?
那滋味是怎样的？

890
01:18:00,600 --> 01:18:04,920
Of course not. It never happens. Sorry.
That's a dumb question. Skip that.
当然不知道，因从没发生
抱歉，这条问题真笨

891
01:18:09,760 --> 01:18:12,240
There you go. Have a nice day.
祝你愉快

892
01:18:27,080 --> 01:18:30,120
Municipal bonds, Ted.
I'm talking double "A" rating.
泰德，你实在很出色

893
01:18:30,360 --> 01:18:32,360
Best investment in America.
是美国最佳的投资

894
01:19:36,200 --> 01:19:39,520
完

895
01:23:50,600 --> 01:23:54,440
Well, I'll give him
another 20 minutes, but that's it.
我只会再给他二十分钟

896
01:23:54,540 --> 01:23:55,630
ENGLISH

